  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Worships at Gibeon'
      title: Solomon Worships at Gibeon
      number: 1
      content: '  Solomon the son of David established himself securely over his
        kingdom, and the Lord his God was with him and made him exceedingly great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Solomon spoke to all Israel, to the commanders of thousands and of
        hundreds and to the judges and to every leader in all Israel, the heads of
        the fathers\u2019 (ancestors\u2019) households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Solomon and all the assembly went to the high place at Gibeon
        [to offer sacrifices, where the Canaanites had habitually worshiped], for
        God\u2019s Tent of Meeting was there, which Moses the servant of the Lord
        had made in the wilderness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But David had brought up the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim to the
        place he had prepared for it, because he had pitched a tent for it in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the bronze altar, which Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur,
        had made was there before the tabernacle of the Lord, and Solomon and the
        assembly sought it out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Solomon went up to the bronze altar before the Lord at the Tent
        of Meeting, and offered a thousand burnt offerings on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Solomon\u2019s Prayer for Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer for Wisdom"
      number: 7
      content: "That night God appeared to Solomon and said to him, \u201CAsk what
        I shall give to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Solomon said to God, \u201CYou have shown great lovingkindness
        and mercy to my father David, and have made me king in his place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now, O Lord God, Your promise to my father David is fulfilled, for
        You have made me king over a people as numerous as the dust of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Give me wisdom and knowledge, so that I may go out and come in [performing
        my duties] before this people, for [otherwise] who can rule and administer
        justice to this great people of Yours?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "God replied to Solomon, \u201CBecause this was in your heart and
        you did not ask for riches, possessions or honor and personal glory, or the
        life of those who hate you, nor have you even asked for long life, but you
        have asked for wisdom and knowledge for yourself so that you may rule and
        administer justice to My people over whom I have made you king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "wisdom and knowledge have been granted you. I will also give you
        riches, possessions, and honor, such as none of the kings who were before
        you has possessed nor will those who will come after you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Solomon\u2019s Wealth"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wealth"
      number: 13
      content: 'So Solomon went from the high place at Gibeon, from the Tent of Meeting,
        to Jerusalem. And he reigned over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Solomon acquired chariots and horsemen; he had 1,400 chariots and
        12,000 horsemen, and he stationed them in the cities [suited for the use]
        of chariots and with the king at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The king made silver and gold as plentiful and common in Jerusalem
        as stones, and he made cedar as plentiful as the sycamore-fig trees in the
        lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Solomon\u2019s horses were imported from Egypt and from Kue. The
        king\u2019s merchants purchased them [in large numbers] from Kue at a price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And they imported chariots from Egypt for 600 shekels of silver apiece,
        and horses for 150 apiece; and in the same way they exported horses to all
        the kings of the Hittites and the kings of the Arameans (Syrians).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Will Build a Temple and Palace'
      title: Solomon Will Build a Temple and Palace
      number: 1
      content: '    Now Solomon decided to build a house (temple) for the Name of
        the Lord, and a royal palace for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Solomon assigned 70,000 men to carry loads, 80,000 men to quarry
        stone in the mountains, and 3,600 to supervise them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Solomon sent word to Hiram king of Tyre, saying, \u201CAs you
        dealt with my father David and sent him cedars to build himself a house in
        which to live, [please] do the same for me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Observe, I am about to build a house for the Name of the Lord my
        God, dedicated to Him, to burn fragrant incense [of sweet spices] before
        Him, to set out the showbread continually, and to offer burnt offerings morning
        and evening, on Sabbaths, New Moons, and on the festivals of the Lord our
        God, as ordained forever in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The house I am going to build will be great, for our God is greater
        than all the gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But who is able to build a house for Him, since the heavens and [even]
        the highest heavens cannot contain Him? Who am I to build a house for Him,
        except [as a place] to burn incense before Him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now send me a man who is skilled to work in gold, silver, bronze,
        and iron, and in purple, crimson, and blue fabrics, and who knows how to
        make engravings, to work with the skilled men who are with me in Judah and
        Jerusalem, whom my father David provided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Send me also cedar, cypress, and algum timber, for I know that your
        servants know how to cut timber in Lebanon. And indeed my servants will work
        with your servants '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'to prepare for me an abundance of timber, because the house I am
        about to build will be great and wonderful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Hiram to Assist'
      title: Hiram to Assist
      number: 10
      content: "And I will give to your servants who cut timber, 20,000 measures
        of crushed wheat and 20,000 measures of barley, and 20,000 baths of wine
        and 20,000 baths of [olive] oil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Hiram, king of Tyre replied in a letter sent to Solomon: \u201CBecause
        the Lord loves His people, He has made you king over them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Hiram said also, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, who
        made heaven and earth, who has given King David a wise son, endowed with
        discretion and understanding, who will build a house for the Lord and a royal
        palace for himself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CNow I am sending a skilled man, endowed with understanding,
        Huram-abi, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the son of a Danite woman and a Tyrian father. He is trained to work
        in gold, silver, bronze, iron, stone, and wood; in purple, blue, and crimson
        fabrics, and in fine linen. He is able to make any kind of engraving and
        to carry out any design given him. He will work with your skilled men and
        those of my lord, David your father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now then, let my lord send to his servants the wheat, the barley,
        the oil, and the wine of which he has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "We will cut whatever timber you need from Lebanon and bring it to
        you on rafts by sea to Joppa, so that you may take it up to Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Solomon took a count of all the aliens in the land of Israel,
        like the census that his father David had taken; and they were found to be
        153,600. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He assigned 70,000 of them to carry loads and 80,000 to quarry stone
        in the mountain, and 3,600 as overseers to make the people work.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Temple Construction in Jerusalem'
      title: The Temple Construction in Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Solomon began to build the house of the Lord in Jerusalem
        on Mount Moriah, where the Lord appeared to his father David, in the place
        that David had prepared, on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Dimensions and Materials of the Temple'
      title: Dimensions and Materials of the Temple
      number: 2
      content: 'Solomon began to build on the second day of the second month in the
        fourth year of his reign.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now this is the [measurement of the] foundation which Solomon laid
        for the house of God: the length in cubits\u2014by the old standard of measure\u2014was
        sixty cubits (90 ft.), and the width was twenty cubits (30 ft.). "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The porch in front of the house was as long as the width of the house,
        twenty cubits, and the height was 120 cubits. He overlaid it inside with
        pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He overlaid the main room [the Holy Place] with cypress wood and
        overlaid it with fine gold, and decorated it with palm trees and chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he adorned the house with precious stones; and the gold was gold
        from Parvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He also overlaid the house [the Holy Place] with gold\u2014the beams,
        the thresholds, and its walls and its doors; and he carved cherubim on the
        walls.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now he made the room of the Holy of Holies: its length equaling the
        width of the house was twenty cubits, and its width was twenty cubits; and
        he overlaid it with 600 talents of fine gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The weight of the nails was fifty shekels of gold. He also overlaid
        the upper rooms with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And in the Holy of Holies he made two sculptured cherubim, and overlaid
        them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The wingspan of the cherubim was twenty cubits: one wing of one cherub
        was five cubits, reaching to the wall of the house, and its other wing, of
        five cubits, touched the other cherub\u2019s wing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The wing of the other cherub, of five cubits, touched the wall of
        the house; and its other wing of five cubits touched the wing of the first
        cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The wings of these cherubim extended twenty cubits. The cherubim
        stood on their feet, their faces toward the Holy Place (the main room). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He made the veil [between the Holy Place and the Holy of Holies]
        of blue, purple, and crimson colors, and fine linen, and embroidered cherubim
        on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He also made two pillars for the front of the house, thirty-five
        cubits high, and the capital on the top of each one was five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He made chains [like a necklace] in the inner sanctuary and put them
        on the tops of the pillars; and he made a hundred pomegranates and put them
        on the chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He erected the pillars in front of the temple, one on the right, the
        other on the left, and named the one on the right Jachin (may He establish)
        and the one on the left Boaz (in Him is strength).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Furnishings of the Temple'
      title: Furnishings of the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Solomon made an altar of bronze, twenty cubits in length,
        twenty cubits in width, and ten cubits in height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He also made the Sea [that is, the large basin used for ceremonial
        washing] of cast metal, ten cubits from brim to brim, circular in form, and
        five cubits in height, and its circumference was thirty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Under it and entirely encircling it were figures of oxen, ten to
        a cubit. The oxen were in two rows, cast in one piece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three
        facing south, three facing east; and the Sea was set on top of them and all
        their hindquarters turned inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It was a handbreadth (the width of the four fingers) thick; its brim
        was made like the brim of a cup, like a lily blossom. It could hold 3,000
        baths (measures). '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also made ten [portable] basins in which to wash, and he put five
        on the right (south) side and five on the left (north). They would rinse
        things for the burnt offering in them, but the Sea was for the priests to
        wash in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he made ten golden lampstands just as directed and set them in
        the temple, five on the right side and five on the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He made also ten tables and placed them in the temple, five on the
        right side and five on the left side, and he made a hundred [ceremonial]
        basins of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moreover, he made the courtyard of the priests, and the great courtyard
        [for the people] and doors for the courtyard, and he overlaid their doors
        with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He set the Sea on the right side at the southeast corner [of the
        house].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Huram also made the pails [for ashes], the shovels, and the basins.
        So Huram finished the work that he did for King Solomon in the house of God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the two pillars, the bowls, the capitals on top of the two pillars,
        and the two lattice works to cover the two bowls of the capitals which were
        on top of the pillars, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and the four hundred pomegranates for the two lattice works, two
        rows of pomegranates for each lattice to cover the two bowls of the capitals
        on the pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He also made the stands and he made the basins on the stands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the one Sea with the twelve oxen under it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The pails, the shovels, and the meat-forks, and all the utensils
        Huram-abi made of polished bronze for King Solomon for the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The king cast them on the plain of the Jordan, in the clay ground
        between Succoth and Zeredah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Solomon made all these utensils in such great quantity that the weight
        of the bronze could not be determined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Solomon also made all the articles that were in the house of God:
        the golden altar, and the tables for the bread of the Presence (showbread), '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and the lampstands with their lamps of pure gold, to burn in front
        of the inner sanctuary (the Holy of Holies) as directed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs of gold, of purest gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: and the snuffers, the basins, the dishes [for incense], and the firepans,
        of pure gold; and for the entrance of the house (temple), the inner doors
        for the Holy of Holies and the doors of the Holy Place (main room), were
        of gold.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Is Brought into the Temple'
      title: The Ark Is Brought into the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus all the work that Solomon did for the house of the Lord was
        finished. He brought in the things that his father David had dedicated, and
        he put the silver and the gold and all the utensils in the treasuries of
        the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of
        the tribes, the leaders of the fathers\u2019 households of the Israelites,
        in Jerusalem to bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord up from the City
        of David, which is Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the men of Israel gathered before the king at the feast in the
        seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And all the elders of Israel came, and the Levites took up the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Levitical priests brought up the ark, the Tent of Meeting, and
        all the holy utensils that were in the Tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And King Solomon and all the assembly of Israel who gathered together
        with him before the ark were sacrificing so many sheep and oxen that they
        could not be counted or numbered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the Lord to its
        place, to the inner sanctuary of the house, into the Holy of Holies, under
        the wings of the cherubim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'for the cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark,
        making a covering above the ark and its carrying poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The poles were so long that the ends of the poles of the ark were
        visible from the front of the Holy of Holies (inner sanctuary), but were
        not visible from the outside. They are there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Glory of God Fills the Temple'
      title: The Glory of God Fills the Temple
      number: 10
      content: 'There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets [of the Ten Commandments]
        which Moses put there at Mount Horeb, when the Lord made a covenant with
        the Israelites, when they came out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the priests came out of the Holy Place (for all the priests
        who were present had sanctified themselves [separating themselves from everything
        unclean], without regard to their assigned divisions), '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and all of the Levitical singers, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun, with
        their sons and relatives, clothed in fine linen, with cymbals, harps, and
        lyres were standing at the east end of the altar, and with them a hundred
        and twenty priests blowing trumpets '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "in unison when the trumpeters and singers were to make themselves
        heard with one voice praising and thanking the Lord, and when they raised
        their voices accompanied by the trumpets and cymbals and [other] instruments
        of music, and when they praised the Lord, saying, \u201CFor He is good, for
        His mercy and lovingkindness endure forever,\u201D then the house of the
        Lord was filled with a cloud, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: so that the priests could not remain standing to minister because
        of the cloud; for the glory and brilliance of the Lord filled the house of
        God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Dedication"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Dedication"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Solomon said,\u201CThe Lord has said that He would dwell in
        the thick cloud.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I have built You a lofty house,A place for You to dwell forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king turned around and blessed the entire assembly of Israel,
        while they were all standing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, who spoke
        with His mouth to my father David and has fulfilled with His hands what He
        promised, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Since the day that I brought My people out of the land of Egypt,
        I did not choose a city among all the tribes of Israel in which to build
        a house so that My Name (Presence) might be there, nor did I choose any man
        to be a leader over My people Israel; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but I have chosen Jerusalem that My Name might be there, and I have
        chosen David to be over My people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a house for the
        Name of the Lord, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the Lord said to my father David, \u2018Because it was in your
        heart to build a house for My Name, you did well that it was in your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Nevertheless you shall not build the house, but your son who will
        be born to you, he shall build the house for My Name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Lord has fulfilled His word which He spoke; for I have risen
        in place of my father David and I sit on the throne of Israel, just as the
        Lord promised, and have built the house for the Name of the Lord, the God
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      number: 11
      content: "There I have placed the ark [the symbol of His Presence] in which
        is the covenant of the Lord [the Ten Commandments], which He made with the
        people (descendants) of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of the Lord in the presence of
        the entire assembly of Israel and spread out his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For Solomon had made a bronze platform, five cubits square and three
        cubits high, and had set it in the midst of the courtyard; and he stood on
        it, and he knelt down on his knees in the presence of all the assembly of
        Israel and spread out his hands toward heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and he said, \u201CO Lord, God of Israel, there is no god like You
        in heaven or on the earth, keeping covenant and showing mercy and lovingkindness
        to Your servants who walk before You [in obedience] with all their heart, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '[You] who have kept Your promise to Your servant David, my father,
        that which You told him; You have spoken with Your mouth and have fulfilled
        it with Your hand, as it is today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore, O Lord, the God of Israel, keep with Your servant
        David, my father, that which You promised him, saying, \u2018You shall not
        fail to have a man to sit on the throne of Israel, provided your sons are
        careful to walk in My law as you, [David,] have walked before Me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now then, O Lord, the God of Israel, let Your word which You have
        spoken to Your servant David be confirmed (verified).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut will God actually dwell with mankind on the earth? Behold,
        heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain You; how much less this house
        which I have built! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet have regard for the prayer of Your servant and for his supplication,
        O Lord my God, to listen to the cry and to the prayer which Your servant
        prays before You, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that Your eyes may be open toward this house day and night, toward
        the place in which You have said that You would put Your Name (Presence),
        to listen to the prayer which Your servant shall pray toward this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So listen to the requests of Your servant and Your people Israel
        when they pray toward this place. Hear from Your dwelling place, from heaven;
        and when You hear, forgive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf a man sins against his neighbor, and he is required to take
        an oath, and he comes and takes the oath before Your altar in this house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'then hear from heaven and act and judge Your servants, punishing
        the wicked by bringing his conduct on his own head, and providing justice
        to the righteous by giving to him in accordance with his righteousness (innocence).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf Your people Israel have been defeated by an enemy because
        they have sinned against You, and they return to You and confess Your name,
        and pray and make supplication before You in this house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of Your people Israel,
        and bring them again to the land which You gave to them and to their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CWhen the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because Your
        people have sinned against You, and they pray toward this place and confess
        Your name, and turn from their sin when You afflict and humble them; "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of Your servants and Your
        people Israel, indeed, teach them the good way in which they should walk.
        And send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people as an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence, if
        there is blight or mildew, if there are [migratory] locusts or grasshoppers,
        if their enemies besiege them in the land of their cities, whatever plague
        or whatever sickness there is,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'then whatever prayer or request is made by any man or all of Your
        people Israel, each knowing his own suffering and his own pain, and stretching
        out his hands toward this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'then hear from heaven, Your dwelling place, and forgive, and render
        to each in accordance with all his ways, whose heart You know; for You alone
        know the hearts of the sons of men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'so that they may fear You, to walk in Your ways [in obedience to
        You] as long as they live in the land which You have given to our fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CAlso in regard to the foreigner who is not from Your people
        Israel, but has come from a far country for the sake of Your great name and
        Your mighty power and Your outstretched arm\u2014when they come and pray
        toward this house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'then hear from heaven, from Your dwelling place, and do according
        to all for which the foreigner calls to You, so that all the peoples of the
        earth may know Your name, and fear You [reverently and worshipfully], as
        do Your people Israel, and that they may know that this house which I have
        built is called by Your Name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CWhen Your people go out to war against their enemies, by the
        way that You send them, and they pray to You facing this city [Jerusalem]
        which You have chosen and the house which I have built for Your Name, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'then hear from heaven their prayer and their request, and maintain
        their cause and do justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CWhen they sin against You (for there is no man who does not
        sin) and You are angry with them and hand them over to an enemy, so that
        they take them away captive to a land far away or near, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "if they take it to heart in the land where they have been taken captive,
        and repent and pray to You in the land of their captivity, saying, \u2018We
        have sinned, we have done wrong and have acted wickedly\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'if they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul
        in the land of their captivity, and pray facing their land which You have
        given to their fathers and toward the city which You have chosen, and toward
        the house which I have built for Your Name; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear from heaven, from Your dwelling place, their prayer and
        requests, and maintain their cause and do justice and forgive Your people
        who have sinned against You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  \u201CNow, O my God, I pray, let Your eyes be open and Your ears
        attentive to the prayer offered in this place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CNow then arise, O Lord God, [and come] to Your resting place,
        You and the ark of Your strength and power. Let Your priests, O Lord God,
        be clothed with salvation and let Your godly ones rejoice in [Your] goodness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CO Lord God, do not turn away and reject the face of Your anointed;
        remember Your lovingkindness and faithfulness to Your servant David.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Shekinah Glory'
      title: The Shekinah Glory
      number: 1
      content: '  When Solomon had finished praying, fire came down from heaven and
        consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices, and the [Shekinah] glory
        and brilliance of the Lord filled the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The priests could not enter the house of the Lord because the glory
        and brilliance of the Lord had filled the Lord\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Sacrifices Offered'
      title: Sacrifices Offered
      number: 3
      content: "When all the people of Israel saw how the fire came down and saw
        the glory and brilliance of the Lord upon the house, they bowed down on the
        stone pavement with their faces to the ground, and they worshiped and praised
        the Lord, saying, \u201CFor He is good, for His mercy and lovingkindness
        endure forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the king and all the people offered a sacrifice before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "King Solomon offered a sacrifice of 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep.
        In this way the king and all the people dedicated God\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The priests stood at their posts [ready for service], and the Levites
        also, with the musical instruments of the Lord which King David had made
        to praise the Lord, saying, \u201CFor His lovingkindness and mercy endure
        forever,\u201D whenever David offered praise through their ministry. The
        priests were opposite the Levites blowing the trumpets and all Israel was
        standing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Feast of Dedication'
      title: The Feast of Dedication
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, Solomon consecrated the middle of the courtyard that was
        in front of the house of the Lord, for it was there that he offered burnt
        offerings and the fat of the peace offerings because the bronze altar which
        he had made was not sufficient to hold the burnt offerings, the grain offerings,
        and the fat [all together].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time Solomon observed the feast for seven days, and all Israel
        with him, a very large assembly, from the entrance of Hamath to the Brook
        of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'On the eighth day they held a celebration, for they had observed
        the dedication of the altar for seven days, and the feast for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: God\u2019s Promise and Warning"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise and Warning"
      number: 10
      content: 'And on the twenty-third day of the seventh month Solomon sent the
        people to their tents, rejoicing and happy in heart because of the goodness
        that the Lord had shown to David, to Solomon, and to His people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so Solomon finished the house (temple) of the Lord and the palace
        of the king. He successfully accomplished all that he had planned to do in
        the house of the Lord and in his palace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord appeared to Solomon by night and said to him: \u201CI
        have heard your prayer and have chosen this place for Myself as a house of
        sacrifice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If I shut up the heavens so that no rain falls, or if I command locusts
        to devour the land, or if I send pestilence and plague among My people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and My people, who are called by My Name, humble themselves, and
        pray and seek (crave, require as a necessity) My face and turn from their
        wicked ways, then I will hear [them] from heaven, and forgive their sin and
        heal their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now My eyes will be open and My ears attentive to prayer offered
        in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For now I have chosen and sanctified and set apart for My purpose
        this house that My Name may be here forever, and My eyes and My heart will
        be here perpetually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for you [Solomon], if you will walk before me as your father David
        walked, and do everything that I have commanded you, and observe My statutes
        and My ordinances, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "then I will establish your royal throne just as I covenanted with
        your father David, saying, \u2018You will not fail to have a man as ruler
        in Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBut if you [people] turn away and abandon My statutes and My
        commandments which I have set before you, and you go and serve other gods
        and worship them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'then I will uproot Israel from My land which I have given them; and
        I will cast this house, which I have consecrated for My Name, out of My sight,
        and will make it a proverb and an object of scorn among all nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And as for this house, which was so exalted, everyone who passes
        by it will be astonished and appalled and say, \u2018Why has the Lord done
        thus to this land and to this house?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then people will say, \u2018It is because they abandoned the Lord,
        the God of their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and
        they adopted other gods, and worshiped them and served them; therefore He
        has brought all this adversity and evil on them.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Activities and Accomplishments"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Activities and Accomplishments"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came about at the end of the twenty years, in which Solomon
        had built the house of the Lord and his own house (palace), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that he built and fortified the cities which Huram (Hiram) had given
        to him, and settled the Israelites there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Solomon went to Hamath-zobah and captured it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all his storage cities in
        Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also built upper Beth-horon and lower Beth-horon, fortified cities
        with walls, gates, and bars [to lock the gates]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Baalath and all the storage cities that Solomon had, and all
        the cities for his chariots and the cities for his horsemen, and all that
        Solomon desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land under
        his rule.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the people who were left of the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites,
        the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who were not of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "but were descendants of those who were left in the land, whom the
        Israelites had not destroyed\u2014Solomon brought them up as forced laborers
        to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Solomon did not make slaves of the Israelites for his work; they
        were men of war, his chief captains, and commanders of his chariots and his
        horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'These were the chief officers of King Solomon, two hundred and fifty
        [in authority] who ruled over the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Solomon brought the daughter of Pharaoh up from the City of
        David into the house (palace) he had built for her, for he said, \u201CMy
        wife shall not live in the house of David king of Israel, because the places
        where the ark of the Lord has entered are holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon offered burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of
        the Lord which he had built in front of the porch [of the temple], '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "a certain number every day, offering them up as Moses commanded for
        the Sabbaths, the New Moons, and the three annual feasts\u2014the Feast of
        Unleavened Bread, the Feast of Weeks, and the Feast of Booths (Tabernacles).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now in accordance with the ordinance of his father David, he appointed
        the divisions of the priests for their service, and the Levites for their
        duties of praise and ministering and serving before the priests as every
        day required, and the gatekeepers by their divisions at every gate; for David
        the man of God had so commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they did not deviate from the commandment of the king to the
        priests and Levites in any respect or in regard to the storehouses or treasuries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Thus all the work of Solomon was carried out from the day the foundation
        of the house of the Lord was laid until it was finished. So the house of
        the Lord was completed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Solomon went to Ezion-geber and to Eloth on the shore of the
        [Red] Sea in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Huram (Hiram) sent him, by his servants, ships and servants familiar
        with the sea; and they went with Solomon\u2019s servants to Ophir, and took
        from there four hundred and fifty talents of gold, and brought them to King
        Solomon."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Visit of the Queen of Sheba'
      title: Visit of the Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: '  When the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came
        to Jerusalem to test Solomon with riddles. She was accompanied by a very
        large number of attendants, with camels bearing spices (balsam oil) and a
        large amount of gold and precious stones. And when she came to Solomon, she
        talked with him about all that was on her mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Solomon answered all her questions; nothing was hidden from him which
        he did not make clear to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So when the queen of Sheba saw the [depth of] Solomon\u2019s wisdom,
        and the house which he had built, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the food of his table, the [vast] seating order of his officials,
        the attendance and service of his ministers and their attire, his cupbearers
        and their attire, and his stairway by which he went up to the house of the
        Lord, she was breathless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "She said to the king, \u201CThe report which I heard in my own land
        regarding your [accomplishments and your] words and your wisdom was true, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but I did not believe the reports until I came and saw it with my
        own eyes. Behold, the half of the greatness of your wisdom was not told to
        me; you have surpassed the report that I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Blessed and fortunate are your people, how blessed and fortunate
        are these servants of yours who stand before you continually and hear your
        wisdom! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Blessed be the Lord your God, who delighted in you, setting you on
        His throne as king for the Lord your God; because your God loved Israel,
        establishing them forever, therefore He made you king over them, to do justice
        and righteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then she gave the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold, a very
        large amount of spices (balsam oil) and precious stones; there was no such
        spice [anywhere] like that which the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The servants of Huram and those of Solomon, who brought gold from
        Ophir, also brought almug trees and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "From the almug timber the king made stairways for the house of the
        Lord and for the king\u2019s palace, and lyres and harps for the singers;
        none like that was seen before in the land of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Solomon\u2019s Wealth and Power"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wealth and Power"
      number: 12
      content: 'King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all [the things] she desired,
        whatever she asked, besides a return for what she had brought to the king.
        So she returned to her own land with her servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the weight of gold which came to Solomon in one year was 666
        talents, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'besides what the traders and merchants brought; and all the kings
        of Arabia and the governors of the country brought gold and silver to Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'King Solomon made two hundred large shields of beaten gold, using
        six hundred shekels of beaten gold on each large shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he made three hundred [smaller] shields of beaten gold, using
        three hundred shekels of gold on each shield; and the king put them in the
        house of the Forest of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover, the king made a great throne of ivory and overlaid it with
        pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There were six steps to the throne and a golden footstool attached
        to the throne, and arms on each side of the seat, with two lions standing
        beside the arms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Also, twelve lions were standing there, one on each side of the six
        steps. Nothing like it had ever been made for any [other] kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "All King Solomon\u2019s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the
        vessels of the house of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold; silver was
        not considered valuable in the days of Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For the king\u2019s ships went to Tarshish with the servants of Huram;
        once every three years the ships of Tarshish came bringing gold and silver,
        ivory and apes and peacocks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So King Solomon surpassed all the kings of the earth in wealth and
        wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And all the kings of the earth were seeking the presence of Solomon,
        to hear his wisdom which God had put into his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Each man brought his gift, articles of silver and gold, garments,
        weapons, spices, horses and mules, so much year by year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now Solomon had 4,000 stalls for horses and chariots, and 12,000
        horsemen, and he stationed them in the chariot cities or with the king at
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He ruled over all the kings from the Euphrates River to the land
        of the Philistines, and as far as the border of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The king made silver in Jerusalem as common as stones, and cedar
        wood as plentiful as the sycamore-fig trees that are in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they were importing horses for Solomon from Egypt and from all
        [the other] countries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, from the first to the last,
        are they not written in the records of Nathan the prophet, and in the prophecy
        of Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Death of Solomon'
      title: Death of Solomon
      number: 30
      content: 'Solomon reigned forty years in Jerusalem over all Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And Solomon slept with his fathers [in death]; he was buried in the
        city of his father David. Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Rehoboam\u2019s Reign of Folly"
      title: "Rehoboam\u2019s Reign of Folly"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Rehoboam went to Shechem, because all Israel had come to Shechem
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard about the new king (for he was
        in Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of King Solomon), Jeroboam
        returned from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the people sent messengers and summoned him. So when Jeroboam
        and all Israel came, they spoke to Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYour father [King Solomon] made our yoke hard (heavy, difficult);
        so now lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke which he
        put on us, and we will serve you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Rehoboam replied, \u201CCome back to me again in three days.\u201D
        So the people departed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then King Rehoboam consulted with the elders who had served his father
        Solomon [as advisers] while he was alive, asking, \u201CWhat advice do you
        give me in answer to these people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They answered him, saying, \u201CIf you are kind to these people
        and please them and speak good words to them, then they will be your servants
        forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the king rejected the advice which the elders gave him, and consulted
        with the young men who grew up with him and served him [as advisers]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He asked them, \u201CWhat advice do you give to us regarding the
        answer to these people, who have spoken to me, saying, \u2018Lighten the
        yoke which your father put on us\u2019?\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The young men who grew up with him told him, \u201CTell the people
        who said to you, \u2018Your father made our yoke heavy, but you make it lighter
        for us\u2019: \u2018My little finger is thicker than my father\u2019s loins! "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now my father loaded you with a heavy yoke, but I will add [more
        weight] to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline
        you with scorpions (extremely painful scourges).\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So on the third day Jeroboam and all the people returned to Rehoboam
        just as the king had directed, saying, \u201CReturn to me on the third day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The king answered them harshly, for King Rehoboam rejected the counsel
        of the elders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He spoke to them in accordance with the advice of the young men,
        saying, \u201CMy father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it; my father
        disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king did not listen to the people, for the turn of events
        was from God that the Lord might fulfill His word, which He had spoken through
        Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When all Israel saw that the king did not listen and pay attention
        to them, the people answered him,\u201CWhat portion do we have in David? 
        We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse.Every man to your tents, O Israel;Now,
        [Rehoboam, descendant of] David, see to your own house.\u201DSo all Israel
        went to their tents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But as for the Israelites who lived in Judah\u2019s cities, Rehoboam
        ruled over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then King Rehoboam sent Hadoram, who was over the forced labor, and
        the Israelites stoned him and he died. And King Rehoboam hurried to mount
        his [royal] chariot to escape to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And Israel has rebelled against the house of David to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rehoboam Reigns over Judah and Builds Cities'
      title: Rehoboam Reigns over Judah and Builds Cities
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled the house of
        Judah and Benjamin, 180,000 chosen warriors to fight against [the ten tribes
        of] Israel to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the word of the Lord came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CSay to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all
        Israel in Judah and Benjamin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CYou shall not go up nor fight against
        your brothers (countrymen); return, every man to his house, for this thing
        is from Me.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D And they listened to and obeyed
        the words of the Lord and turned back from going against Jeroboam.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Rehoboam lived in Jerusalem and built [fortified] cities for defense
        in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Beth-zur, Soco, Adullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gath, Mareshah, Ziph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, which are fortified cities in Judah and
        Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He strengthened the fortresses and put officers in them, with supplies
        of food, [olive] oil, and wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And in each city he put [large] shields and spears, and made them
        very strong. So he held Judah and Benjamin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jeroboam Appoints False Priests'
      title: Jeroboam Appoints False Priests
      number: 13
      content: 'Further, the priests and the Levites who were in all Israel took
        their stand with Rehoboam from all their districts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the Levites left their pasture lands and their property and came
        to Judah and Jerusalem, because Jeroboam and his sons had excluded them from
        serving as priests to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Jeroboam appointed his own priests for the high places, for the satyrs
        (goat demons) and calves (idols) which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Those from all the tribes of Israel who set their hearts on seeking
        the Lord God of Israel followed them to Jerusalem, to sacrifice to the Lord
        God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Rehoboam\u2019s Family"
      title: "Rehoboam\u2019s Family"
      number: 17
      content: 'So they strengthened the kingdom of Judah and supported Rehoboam
        the son of Solomon for three years; for they walked in the way of David and
        Solomon for three years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Rehoboam took as his wife Mahalath, the daughter of Jerimoth the
        son of David, and of Abihail the daughter of Eliab the son of Jesse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She bore him sons: Jeush, Shemariah, and Zaham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After her he took Maacah the daughter (granddaughter) of Absalom,
        and she bore him Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Rehoboam loved Maacah the daughter (granddaughter) of Absalom more
        than all his wives and concubines\u2014for he had taken eighteen wives and
        sixty concubines, and he fathered twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maacah the chief leader among
        his brothers, because he intended to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He acted wisely and distributed some of his sons throughout the territories
        of Judah and Benjamin to all the fortified cities. He gave them abundant
        provisions, and he sought many wives for them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Shishak of Egypt Invades Judah'
      title: Shishak of Egypt Invades Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  When the kingdom of Rehoboam was established and strong, he and
        all Israel with him abandoned the law of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it came about in King Rehoboam\u2019s fifth year, because they
        had been unfaithful to the Lord, that Shishak king of Egypt came up against
        Jerusalem "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "with 1,200 chariots and 60,000 horsemen. The people who came with
        him from Egypt were beyond counting\u2014the Lubim, the Sukkiim, and the
        Ethiopians. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Shishak took the fortified cities of Judah and came as far as Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam and the leaders of Judah
        who had gathered at Jerusalem because of Shishak, and said to them, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018You have abandoned (turned away from) Me, so I have
        abandoned you into the hands of Shishak.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the leaders of Israel and the king humbled themselves and said,
        \u201CThe Lord is righteous.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the Lord saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the Lord
        came to Shemaiah, saying, \u201CThey have humbled themselves so I will not
        destroy them, but I will grant them some measure of a remnant [that escapes];
        and My wrath shall not be poured out on Jerusalem by means of Shishak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Plunder Impoverishes Judah'
      title: Plunder Impoverishes Judah
      number: 8
      content: "Nevertheless they will become his slaves, so that they may know [the
        difference between] My service and the service of the kingdoms of the countries.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Shishak king of Egypt went up against Jerusalem; he took the treasures
        of the house of the Lord and the treasures of the king\u2019s house (palace).
        He took everything. He even took the shields of gold which Solomon had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In their place King Rehoboam made shields of bronze and entrusted
        them to the care of the officers of the guard who guarded the door of the
        king\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And whenever the king entered the house of the Lord, the guards came
        and carried the shields and then brought them back into the guards\u2019
        room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Rehoboam humbled himself, the wrath of the Lord turned away
        from him, so as not to destroy him completely; and also conditions were good
        in Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So King Rehoboam established himself in Jerusalem and reigned. Rehoboam
        was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen
        years in Jerusalem, the city in which the Lord had chosen from all the tribes
        of Israel to put His Name. And his mother was Naamah the Ammonitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He did evil because he did not set his heart to seek and worship
        and honor the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the acts of Rehoboam, from the first to the last, are they not
        written in the records of Shemaiah the prophet and of Iddo the seer, according
        to genealogical enrollment? There were wars between Rehoboam [of Judah] and
        Jeroboam [of Israel] continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And Rehoboam slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried in the
        City of David; and Abijah his son became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijah Succeeds Rehoboam'
      title: Abijah Succeeds Rehoboam
      number: 1
      content: '  In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, Abijah became king over
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Micaiah
        the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah.  And there was war between Abijah and Jeroboam
        [of Israel]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Civil War'
      title: Civil War
      number: 3
      content: 'Abijah began the battle with an army of brave soldiers, 400,000 chosen
        men. Jeroboam drew up in battle formation against him with 800,000 chosen
        men, valiant men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Abijah stood on Mount Zemaraim, which is in the hill country
        of Ephraim, and said, \u201CListen to me, Jeroboam and all Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do you not know that the Lord God of Israel, gave rule over Israel
        forever to David and to his sons by a covenant of salt [a permanent pact,
        extending to each generation of Israel]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, a servant of Solomon the son of David,
        rose up and rebelled against his lord [the king], '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and worthless (unprincipled, unethical) men gathered around him,
        useless and wicked men, who proved too strong for Rehoboam the son of Solomon
        when Rehoboam was young and timid, and could not assert himself against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd now you intend to assert yourselves against the kingdom
        of the Lord which is in the hands of the sons of David, since you are a great
        multitude and have with you the golden calves (idols) which Jeroboam made
        for you as gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you not driven out the priests of the Lord, the sons of Aaron
        and the Levites, and made priests for yourselves like the peoples of other
        lands? So whoever comes to consecrate himself with a young bull and seven
        rams, even he may become a priest of non-existent gods (idols). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But as for us, the Lord is our God, and we have not abandoned (turned
        away from) Him. The sons of Aaron are ministering to the Lord as priests,
        and the Levites attend to their service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Every morning and every evening they offer the burnt offerings and
        the fragrant incense to the Lord; and the showbread is set on the clean table
        [of pure gold], and the golden lampstand with its lamps is ready to light
        every evening; for we keep the charge of the Lord our God [that is, the obligation
        we have to Him], but you have abandoned (turned away from) Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Behold, God is with us at our head, and His priests [are here] with
        their signal trumpets to sound an alarm against you. O sons of Israel, do
        not fight against the Lord God of your fathers, for you cannot succeed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But Jeroboam had set an ambush to come from the rear, so that Israel
        was in front of Judah and the ambush was behind them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When [the men of] Judah turned around, they were attacked from both
        front and rear; so they cried out to the Lord [for help], and the priests
        blew the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the men of Judah raised a war cry; and as they shouted, God
        struck Jeroboam and all Israel [with defeat] before Abijah and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the sons of Israel fled before Judah, and God handed over the
        sons of Israel to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Abijah and his people inflicted on them a great defeat, so that 500,000
        chosen men of Israel fell slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Thus the sons of Israel were subdued (humbled) at that time, and
        the sons of Judah prevailed because they relied on the Lord, the God of their
        fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Death of Jeroboam'
      title: Death of Jeroboam
      number: 19
      content: 'Abijah pursued Jeroboam and captured [several] cities from him: Bethel,
        Jeshanah, and Ephraim (Ephron), with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Jeroboam did not recover strength again during the time of [the reign
        of] Abijah. And the Lord struck him and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But Abijah became powerful. He took fourteen wives for himself and
        fathered twenty-two sons and sixteen daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Abijah, and his ways and his sayings,
        are written in the writing of the prophet Iddo.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Asa Succeeds Abijah in Judah'
      title: Asa Succeeds Abijah in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    So Abijah slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried
        him in the City of David; and Asa his son became king in his place. The land
        was at peace for ten years during his days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Asa did what was good and right in the sight of the Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He removed the foreign altars and high places and tore down the [pagan]
        pillars (obelisks, memorial stones), and cut to pieces the Asherim [the symbols
        of the goddess Asherah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he commanded Judah to seek the Lord God of their fathers [to
        inquire of and for Him and seek Him as a vital necessity], and to observe
        the law [given to Moses] and the commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Asa also removed the [idolatrous] high places and the incense altars
        from all the cities of Judah. The kingdom was at rest and undisturbed under
        his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He built fortified cities in Judah, since the land was at rest, and
        there was no one at war with him in those years, because the Lord had given
        him rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he said to Judah, \u201CLet us build these cities and surround
        them with walls, towers, gates and bars [to secure the doors]. The land is
        still ours because we have sought the Lord our God; we have sought Him [longing
        for Him with all our heart] and He has given us peace on every side.\u201D
        So they built and prospered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now Asa had an army of 300,000 men from Judah, who carried large
        shields and spears, and 280,000 from Benjamin, who carried shields and drew
        bows, all courageous men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now Zerah the Ethiopian (Cushite) came out against Judah with an
        army of a million men and three hundred chariots, and he came as far as Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Asa went out against him, and they drew up in battle formation
        in the Valley of Zephathah at Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Asa called out to the Lord his God, saying, \u201CO Lord, there is
        no one besides You to help in the battle between the powerful and the weak;
        so help us, O Lord our God, for we trust in and rely on You, and in Your
        name we have come against this multitude. O Lord, You are our God; let not
        man prevail against You.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the Lord struck the Ethiopians [with defeat] before Asa and Judah,
        and the Ethiopians fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Asa and the people who were with him pursued them as far as Gerar;
        and so many Ethiopians fell that none of them were found alive; for they
        were destroyed before the Lord and His army. And they carried away a very
        large amount of spoil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They attacked and destroyed all the cities around Gerar, for the
        dread of the Lord had fallen on them. They plundered all the cities, for
        there was a large amount of spoil in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They also struck down the people [living] in tents who had livestock,
        and took captive large numbers of sheep and camels. Then they returned to
        Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prophet Azariah Warns Asa'
      title: The Prophet Azariah Warns Asa
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Spirit of God came on Azariah the son of Oded, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and he went out to meet Asa and said to him, \u201CHear me, Asa,
        and all Judah and Benjamin: the Lord is with you while you are with Him.
        If you seek Him [inquiring for and of Him, as your soul\u2019s first necessity],
        He will let you find Him; but if you abandon (turn away from) Him, He will
        abandon (turn away from) you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now for a long time Israel was without the true God and without a
        teaching priest, and without [God\u2019s] law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when they were in their trouble and distress they turned to the
        Lord God of Israel, and [in desperation earnestly] sought Him, and He let
        them find Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In those times there was no peace for him who went out or for him
        who came in, for great suffering came on all the inhabitants of the lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nation was crushed by nation, and city by city, for God troubled
        them with every kind of distress. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Asa\u2019s Reforms"
      title: "Asa\u2019s Reforms"
      number: 7
      content: "But as for you, be strong and do not lose courage, for there is reward
        for your work.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Asa heard these words, the prophecy of Azariah the son of
        Oded the prophet, he took courage and removed the repulsive idols from all
        the land of Judah and Benjamin and from the cities which he had captured
        in the hill country of Ephraim. Then he restored the altar [of burnt offering]
        of the Lord which was in front of the porch [of the temple] of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He gathered all Judah and Benjamin and the strangers who were with
        them out of Ephraim, Manasseh, and Simeon, for they came over to Asa from
        Israel in large numbers when they saw that the Lord his God was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they assembled at Jerusalem in the third month of the fifteenth
        year of Asa\u2019s reign. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They sacrificed to the Lord on that day from the spoil they had brought\u2014700
        oxen and 7,000 sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They entered into a covenant (solemn agreement) to seek the Lord
        God of their fathers with all their heart and soul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and that whoever would not seek the Lord God of Israel, was to be
        put to death, whether young or old, man or woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They swore an oath to the Lord with a loud voice, with [jubilant]
        shouting, with trumpets, and with horns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All Judah rejoiced over the oath, for they had sworn with all their
        heart and had sought Him with their whole heart, and He let them find Him.
        So the Lord gave them rest on every side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He also removed Maacah, King Asa\u2019s mother, from the position
        of queen mother, because she had made a repulsive image for [the goddess]
        Asherah. Asa cut down her idol, crushed it, and burned it at the Brook Kidron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the high places [of pagan worship] were not removed from Israel.
        Nevertheless Asa\u2019s heart was blameless all his days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He brought the things that his father [Abijah] had dedicated and
        those things that he had dedicated into the house of God\u2014silver and
        gold and utensils. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And there was no war until the thirty-fifth year of Asa\u2019s reign."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Asa Wars against Baasha'
      title: Asa Wars against Baasha
      number: 1
      content: "  In the thirty-sixth year of Asa\u2019s reign Baasha king of Israel
        came up against Judah and fortified Ramah in order to prevent anyone from
        going out or coming in to [meet with] Asa king of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Asa brought out silver and gold from the treasuries of the house
        of the Lord and from the king\u2019s house, and sent them to Ben-hadad king
        of Aram (Syria), who lived in Damascus, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet there be a treaty between you and me, as there was between
        my father and your father. Look, I am sending you silver and gold; go, break
        your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, so that he will withdraw from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies
        against the cities of Israel; and they attacked and conquered Ijon, Dan,
        Abel-maim, and all the storage cities of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Baasha heard about it, he ceased fortifying Ramah and stopped
        his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Asa Imprisons the Prophet'
      title: Asa Imprisons the Prophet
      number: 6
      content: 'Then King Asa brought all Judah, and they carried away the stones
        of Ramah and its timber with which Baasha had been building, and with them
        he fortified Geba and Mizpah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "At that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah and said to
        him, \u201CBecause you relied on the king of Aram (Syria) and did not rely
        on the Lord your God, the army of the king of Aram (Syria) has escaped out
        of your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Were not the Ethiopians and Lubim a huge army with a great number
        of chariots and horsemen? Yet because you relied on the Lord, He placed them
        in your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the eyes of the Lord move to and fro throughout the earth so
        that He may support those whose heart is completely His. You have acted foolishly
        in this; therefore, from now on you will have wars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Asa was angry with the seer and put him in prison [in the stocks],
        for he was enraged with him because of this. And at the same time Asa oppressed
        some of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the acts of Asa, from the first to the last, are written in the
        Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In the thirty-ninth year of his reign Asa developed a disease in
        his feet. His disease was severe, yet even in his illness he did not seek
        the Lord, but [relied only on] the physicians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Asa slept with his fathers [in death], dying in the forty-first
        year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They buried him in his own tomb which he had cut out for himself
        in the City of David, and they laid him on a bier which he had filled with
        various kinds of spices blended by the perfumers\u2019 art; and they made
        a very great fire in his honor."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoshaphat Succeeds Asa'
      title: Jehoshaphat Succeeds Asa
      number: 1
      content: "  Jehoshaphat his son then became king [of Judah] in Asa\u2019s place,
        and strengthened his position over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: His Good Reign'
      title: His Good Reign
      number: 2
      content: 'He placed troops in all the fortified cities of Judah, and set garrisons
        in the land of Judah and in the cities of Ephraim which his father Asa had
        captured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord was with Jehoshaphat because he followed the example of
        his father (ancestor) David. He did not seek [to follow] the Baals [the false
        gods], '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but sought the God of his father, and walked in (obeyed) His commandments,
        and did not act as Israel did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the Lord established the kingdom in his hand; and all Judah
        brought tribute to Jehoshaphat, and he had great wealth and honor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His heart was encouraged and he took great pride in the ways of the
        Lord; moreover, he again removed the high places [of pagan worship] and the
        Asherim from Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then in the third year of his reign he sent his officials, Ben-hail,
        Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel, and Micaiah, to teach in the cities of Judah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and with them were the Levites\u2014Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah,
        Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah, and Tobadonijah; and
        with them the priests Elishama and Jehoram. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They taught in Judah having the Book of the Law of the Lord with
        them; they went throughout all the cities of Judah and taught among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the dread of the Lord was on all the kingdoms of the lands surrounding
        Judah, so that they did not make war against Jehoshaphat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Some of the Philistines brought gifts and silver as tribute to Jehoshaphat;
        the Arabians also brought him flocks: 7,700 rams and 7,700 male goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Jehoshaphat became greater and greater. He built fortresses and
        storage cities in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He had large supplies in the cities of Judah, and soldiers, courageous
        men, in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "This was the number of them by their fathers\u2019 (ancestors\u2019)
        households: of Judah, the commanders of thousands, Adnah the commander, and
        with him 300,000 courageous men; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and next to him was Jehohanan the commander, and with him 280,000; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and next to him Amasiah the son of Zichri, who volunteered for the
        Lord, and with him 200,000 courageous men; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and of Benjamin: Eliada, a brave man, and with him 200,000 men armed
        with bow and shield; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and next to him was Jehozabad, and with him 180,000 armed and ready
        for military service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: These are the ones who were in the service of the king, besides those
        he had placed in fortified cities throughout Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoshaphat Allies with Ahab'
      title: Jehoshaphat Allies with Ahab
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jehoshaphat had great wealth and honor, and was allied by marriage
        with Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Some years later he went down to [visit] Ahab in Samaria. And Ahab
        slaughtered many sheep and oxen for him and the people who were with him,
        and induced him to go up against Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, \u201CWill
        you go with me to [fight against] Ramoth-gilead?\u201D He answered, \u201CI
        am as you are, and my people as your people [your hopes and concerns are
        ours]; we will be with you in the battle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Further, Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CPlease inquire
        first for the word of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king of Israel assembled the prophets, four hundred men,
        and said to them, \u201CShall we go against Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall
        I refrain?\u201D And they said, \u201CGo up, for God will hand it over to
        the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs there no prophet of the Lord still
        here by whom we may inquire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Ahab\u2019s False Prophets Assure Victory"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s False Prophets Assure Victory"
      number: 7
      content: "The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CThere is still one
        man by whom we may inquire of the Lord, but I hate him, for he never prophesies
        [anything] good for me, but always evil. He is Micaiah the son of Imla\u201D
        And Jehoshaphat said, \u201CLet not the king say so [perhaps this time it
        will be different].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king of Israel called for an officer and said, \u201CBring
        Micaiah the son of Imla quickly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting,
        each on his throne, arrayed in their robes; they were sitting at the threshing
        floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets were prophesying
        before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah had made horns of iron for himself;
        and said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018With these you shall gore the Arameans
        (Syrians) until they are destroyed.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Micaiah Brings Word from God'
      title: Micaiah Brings Word from God
      number: 11
      content: "All the prophets prophesied this, saying, \u201CGo up to Ramoth-gilead
        and succeed; the Lord will hand it over to the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The messenger who went to call Micaiah said to him, \u201CListen,
        the words of the prophets are of one accord, foretelling a favorable outcome
        for the king. So just let your word be like one of them and speak favorably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Micaiah said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, I will [only] speak what
        my God says.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When he came to the king, the king said to him, \u201CMicaiah, shall
        we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall I refrain?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CGo up and succeed, for they will be handed over to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the king said to him, \u201CHow many times must I warn you (make
        you swear an oath) to tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the Lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Micaiah said,\u201CI saw all [the people of] IsraelScattered
        on the mountains,As sheep that have no shepherd;And the Lord said,\u2018These
        have no master.Let each one return to his house in peace.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CDid I not tell
        you that he would not prophesy good in regard to me, but [only] evil?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Micaiah said, \u201CTherefore, hear the word of the Lord: I saw
        the Lord sitting on His throne, and all the host (army) of heaven standing
        on His right and on His left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u2018Who will entice Ahab king of Israel to
        go up and fall [defeated] at Ramoth-gilead?\u2019 And one said this and another
        said that. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then a spirit came forward and stood before the Lord and said, \u2018I
        will entice him.\u2019 The Lord said to him, \u2018By what means?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He said, \u2018I will go out and be a deceptive spirit in the mouth
        of all his prophets.\u2019 Then the Lord said, \u2018You are to entice him
        and also succeed. Go and do so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now, you see, the Lord put a deceptive spirit in the mouth of these
        prophets of yours; and the Lord has [actually] proclaimed disaster against
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came up and struck Micaiah on
        the cheek and said, \u201CWhich way did the Spirit of the Lord go [when he
        departed] from me to speak to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Micaiah said, \u201CBehold, you will see on that day when you go
        into an inner room [desperately trying] to hide yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CTake Micaiah and return him to
        Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king\u2019s son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the king: \u201CPut this man in prison and
        feed him just enough bread and water to survive until I return in peace (safely).\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Ahab\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      number: 27
      content: "But Micaiah said, \u201CIf you actually return in peace, the Lord
        has not spoken by me.\u201D And he added, \u201CListen [to what I have said],
        you people, all of you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So [Ahab] the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up
        against Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CI will disguise myself
        and will go into battle, but you put on your [royal] robes.\u201D So the
        king of Israel disguised himself, and they went into the battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now the king of Aram (Syria) had commanded the captains of his chariots,
        saying, \u201CDo not fight with the small or the great, but only with the
        king of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat [of Judah],
        they said, \u201CIt is the king of Israel!\u201D So they turned to fight
        against him, but Jehoshaphat called out [for God\u2019s help], and the Lord
        helped him; and God diverted them away from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of
        Israel, they turned back from pursuing him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then a certain man drew his bow at random and struck [Ahab] the king
        of Israel between the scales of his armor. So Ahab said to his chariot driver,
        \u201CTurn around and take me out of the battle, because I am seriously wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: The battle raged that day, and the king of Israel propped himself
        up in his chariot in front of the Arameans (Syrians) until the evening, and
        at sunset he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Rebukes Jehoshaphat'
      title: Jehu Rebukes Jehoshaphat
      number: 1
      content: '  Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned safely to his house (palace)
        in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him and said to
        King Jehoshaphat, \u201CShould you help the ungodly and love those who hate
        the Lord and in doing so bring wrath from the Lord on yourself? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But there are some good things found in you, for you have removed
        the Asherim (idols) from the land and you have set your heart to seek God
        [with all your soul\u2019s desire].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Reforms Instituted'
      title: Reforms Instituted
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jehoshaphat lived in Jerusalem, and he went out again among the
        people from Beersheba to the hill country of Ephraim and brought them back
        to the Lord, the God of their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He appointed judges in the land in all the fortified cities of Judah,
        city by city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and he said to the judges, \u201CBe careful what you do, for you
        do not judge for man, but for the Lord who is with you in the matter of judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So now let the fear (reverent awe) of the Lord be on you [to keep
        you from making unjust decisions]; be careful in what you do, for there is
        no injustice with the Lord our God, or partiality, or acceptance of a bribe.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "In Jerusalem also Jehoshaphat appointed some of the Levites, priests,
        and heads of the fathers\u2019 households of Israel to render the judgment
        of the Lord and to judge disputes among the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king commanded them, \u201CDo this in the fear of the Lord,
        faithfully and wholeheartedly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Whenever any dispute comes to you from your brothers (relatives)
        who live in their cities, between blood and blood, between law and commandment,
        or between statutes and judgments, you are to warn [and instruct] them so
        that they may not be guilty before the Lord; otherwise [God\u2019s] wrath
        will come on you and your brothers. Do this and you will not be guilty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Behold, Amariah the chief priest will be over you in all matters
        of the Lord, and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the governor of the house of
        Judah, in all the king\u2019s matters; and the Levites will serve you as
        officers. Deal courageously, and may the Lord be with the upright.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah Invaded'
      title: Judah Invaded
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened after this that the Moabites and the Ammonites,
        together with some of the Meunites, came to make war against Jehoshaphat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then it was reported to Jehoshaphat, \u201CA great multitude has
        come against you from beyond the [Dead] Sea, out of Aram (Syria); and behold,
        they are in Hazazon-tamar (that is, Engedi).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jehoshaphat was afraid and set himself [determinedly, as his
        vital need] to seek the Lord; and he proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Jehoshaphat\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Jehoshaphat\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 4
      content: 'So [the people of] Judah gathered together to seek help from the
        Lord; indeed they came from all the cities of Judah to seek the Lord [longing
        for Him with all their heart].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in
        the house of the Lord in front of the new courtyard, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and said, \u201CO Lord, God of our fathers, are You not God in heaven?
        And do You not rule over all the kingdoms of the nations? Power and might
        are in Your hand, there is no one able to take a stand against You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O our God, did You not drive out the inhabitants of this land before
        Your people Israel and give it forever to the descendants of Your friend
        Abraham? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They have lived in it, and have built You a sanctuary in it for Your
        Name, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018If evil comes on us, or the sword of judgment, or plague, or
        famine, we will stand before this house and before You (for Your Name and
        Your Presence is in this house) and we will cry out to You in our distress,
        and You will hear and save us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now behold, the sons of Ammon and Moab and Mount Seir, whom You would
        not allow Israel to invade when they came from the land of Egypt (for they
        turned away from them and did not destroy them), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'here they are, rewarding us by coming to drive us out of Your possession
        which You have given us as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O our God, will You not judge them? For we are powerless against
        this great multitude which is coming against us. We do not know what to do,
        but our eyes are on You.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jahaziel Answers the Prayer'
      title: Jahaziel Answers the Prayer
      number: 13
      content: 'So all Judah stood before the Lord, with their infants, their wives,
        and their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then in the midst of the assembly the Spirit of the Lord came upon
        Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the
        son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the sons of Asaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CListen carefully, all [you people of] Judah, and you
        inhabitants of Jerusalem, and King Jehoshaphat. The Lord says this to you:
        \u2018Be not afraid or dismayed at this great multitude, for the battle is
        not yours, but God\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Go down against them tomorrow. Behold, they will come up by the ascent
        of Ziz, and you will find them at the end of the river valley, in front of
        the Wilderness of Jeruel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You need not fight in this battle; take your positions, stand and
        witness the salvation of the Lord who is with you, O Judah and Jerusalem.
        Do not fear or be dismayed; tomorrow go out against them, for the Lord is
        with you.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jehoshaphat bowed with his face to the ground, and all Judah and
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell down before the Lord, worshiping Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Enemies Destroy Themselves'
      title: Enemies Destroy Themselves
      number: 19
      content: 'The Levites, from the sons of the Kohathites and the sons of the
        Korahites, stood up to praise the Lord God of Israel, with a very loud voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So they got up early in the morning and went out into the Wilderness
        of Tekoa; and as they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, \u201CHear me,
        O Judah, and you inhabitants of Jerusalem! Believe and trust in the Lord
        your God and you will be established (secure). Believe and trust in His prophets
        and succeed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When he had consulted with the people, he appointed those who sang
        to the Lord and those who praised Him in their holy (priestly) attire, as
        they went out before the army and said, \u201CPraise and give thanks to the
        Lord, for His mercy and lovingkindness endure forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When they began singing and praising, the Lord set ambushes against
        the sons of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah; so they
        were struck down [in defeat]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the sons of Ammon and Moab [suspecting betrayal] rose up against
        the inhabitants of Mount Seir, completely destroying them; and when they
        had finished with the inhabitants of Seir, they helped to destroy one another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When [the men of] Judah came to the lookout tower of the wilderness,
        they looked toward the multitude, and behold, they were dead bodies lying
        on the ground, and no one had escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Triumphant Return to Jerusalem'
      title: Triumphant Return to Jerusalem
      number: 25
      content: 'When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take their spoil, they found
        much among them, including equipment, garments, and valuable things which
        they took for themselves, more than they could carry away; so much that they
        spent three days gathering the spoil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then on the fourth day they assembled in the Valley of Beracah, for
        it was there that they blessed the Lord. For that reason they named that
        place \u201CThe Valley of Beracah (blessing)\u201D until today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then they returned to Jerusalem with joy, every man of Judah and
        Jerusalem, led by Jehoshaphat, for the Lord had made them rejoice over their
        enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They came to Jerusalem with harps, lyres, and trumpets to the house
        (temple) of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the fear of God came on all the kingdoms of those countries when
        they heard that the Lord had fought against the enemies of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the kingdom of Jehoshaphat was quiet, for his God gave him rest
        on all sides.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah. He was thirty-five years old
        when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem for twenty-five years. His
        mother\u2019s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He walked in the way of his father Asa and did not depart from it,
        doing what was right in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Only the high places [for pagan sacrifices] were not removed, for
        the people had not yet set their hearts firmly on the God of their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Alliance Displeases God'
      title: Alliance Displeases God
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, from the first to the last,
        behold, they are written in the records of Jehu the son of Hanani, which
        are recorded in the Book of the Kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'After [all] this Jehoshaphat king of Judah made an alliance with
        Ahaziah king of Israel, and he acted wickedly in doing so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'He joined him in building ships to go to Tarshish [for trade], and
        they built them in Ezion-geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Eliezer the son of Dodavahu of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat,
        saying, \u201CBecause you have allied yourself with Ahaziah, the Lord has
        broken down what you have built.\u201D So the ships were wrecked and were
        unable to go to Tarshish."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoram Succeeds Jehoshaphat in Judah'
      title: Jehoram Succeeds Jehoshaphat in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with
        them in the City of David; and his son Jehoram became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah,
        Azaryahu, Michael, and Shephatiah. All of these were the sons of Jehoshaphat
        king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their father gave them many gifts of silver, gold, and valuable things,
        in addition to fortified cities in Judah; but he gave the kingdom to Jehoram
        because he was the firstborn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When Jehoram had ascended over the kingdom of his father and made
        himself secure, he killed all his brothers with the sword [to eliminate any
        rivals], and some of the leaders of Israel as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoram was thirty-two years of age when he became king, and he reigned
        eight years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house of
        Ahab had done (for he married the daughter of Ahab), and he did what was
        evil in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Revolt against Judah'
      title: Revolt against Judah
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet the Lord would not destroy the house of David because of the
        covenant which He had made with David, and because He had promised to give
        a lamp to him and to his sons forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the days of Jehoram Edom revolted against the rule of Judah and
        set up a king over themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoram crossed over [the Jordan River] with his commanders
        and all his chariots, and rose up by night and struck down the Edomites who
        were surrounding him and the commanders of the chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Edom revolted against the rule of Judah to this day. Then Libnah
        revolted at the same time against Jehoram\u2019s rule, because he had abandoned
        (turned away from) the Lord God of his fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Moreover, he made [idolatrous] high places in the hill country of
        Judah, and caused the inhabitants of Jerusalem to be unfaithful [to God],
        and he led Judah astray [compelling the people\u2019s cooperation].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then a letter came to Jehoram from Elijah the prophet, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord God of David your father (ancestor): \u2018Because you have
        not walked in the ways of your father Jehoshaphat nor in the ways of Asa
        king of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "but have walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and caused Judah
        and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to be unfaithful [to God] as the house of
        Ahab was unfaithful, and you have also murdered your brothers, your father\u2019s
        house (your own family), who were better than you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'behold, the Lord is going to strike your people, your sons, your
        wives, and all your possessions with a great disaster; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and you will suffer a severe illness, an intestinal disease, until
        your intestines come out because of the sickness, day after day.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the Lord stirred up against Jehoram the spirit (anger) of the
        Philistines and of the Arabs who bordered the Ethiopians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They came against Judah and invaded it, and carried away all the
        possessions found in the king\u2019s house (palace), together with his sons
        and his wives; so there was not a son left to him except Jehoahaz, the youngest
        of his sons.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After all this, the Lord struck Jehoram with an incurable intestinal
        disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now it came about in the course of time, at the end of two years,
        that his intestines came out because of his disease and he died in excruciating
        pain. And his people did not make a funeral fire to honor him, like the fire
        for his fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        in Jerusalem eight years; and he departed with no one\u2019s regret (sorrow).
        They buried him in the City of David, but not in the tombs of the kings."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaziah Succeeds Jehoram in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Succeeds Jehoram in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah, his youngest son,
        king in his place, because the band of men (raiders) who came with the Arabs
        to the camp had killed all the older sons. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram
        king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Athaliah, a granddaughter
        of Omri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab, for his mother was
        his adviser [and she encouraged him] to act wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Ahaziah Allies with Jehoram of Israel'
      title: Ahaziah Allies with Jehoram of Israel
      number: 4
      content: 'So he did evil in the sight of the Lord like the house of Ahab, for
        they were his advisers after the death of his father, resulting in his destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also walked in accordance with their advice, and he went with
        Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to wage war against Hazael king of
        Aram (Syria) at Ramoth-gilead. And the Arameans wounded Joram (Jehoram). '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds they had inflicted
        on him at Ramah when he fought against Hazael king of Aram. And Ahaziah,
        the son of Jehoram king of Judah, went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab
        in Jezreel, because he was sick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Jehu Murders Leaders of Judah'
      title: Jehu Murders Leaders of Judah
      number: 7
      content: 'But the downfall of Ahaziah was ordained by God, in that he went
        to Joram (Jehoram). For when he arrived there he went out [as an ally] with
        Jehoram against Jehu the son of Nimshi, whom the Lord had anointed to destroy
        the house of Ahab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It came about that when Jehu was executing judgment on the house
        of Ahab, he found the leaders of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah\u2019s [murdered]
        brothers ministering to Ahaziah, and he killed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jehu also searched for Ahaziah, who was hiding in Samaria; he was
        captured, brought to Jehu, and put to death. They buried him, for they said,
        \u201CAfter all, he is the grandson of Jehoshaphat, who sought the Lord with
        all his heart.\u201D So the house of Ahaziah had no one left to retain the
        power to rule over the kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead,
        she rose and destroyed all the royal family of the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Jehoshabeath, the king\u2019s daughter, took Joash the [infant]
        son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the king\u2019s sons who were
        being put to death, and she placed him and his nurse in the bedroom. So Jehoshabeath,
        the daughter of King Jehoram [of Judah] and wife of Jehoiada the priest,
        hid Joash from [his grandmother] Athaliah so that she did not murder him
        (for Jehoshabeath was the sister of Ahaziah). "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Joash was hidden with them in the house (temple) of God for six years,
        and Athaliah reigned over the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoiada Sets Joash on the Throne of Judah'
      title: Jehoiada Sets Joash on the Throne of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the seventh year Jehoiada [the priest] summoned his courage
        and took the captains of hundreds: Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ishmael the
        son of Johanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and
        Elishaphat the son of Zichri, and they entered into a covenant with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They went throughout Judah and gathered the Levites out of all the
        cities of Judah, and the heads of the households of the fathers (ancestors)
        in Israel, and they came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then all the assembly made a covenant in the house of God with the
        king [that is, with the child Joash, to overthrow Athaliah by proclaiming
        his sovereignty]. And Jehoiada [the priest] said to them, \u201CBehold, the
        king\u2019s son [Joash] shall reign, as the Lord has said in regard to the
        sons of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is what you shall do: a third of you, of the priests and Levites
        who are resuming service on the Sabbath, shall be gatekeepers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "a [second] third shall be at the king\u2019s house (palace), and
        a [final] third at the Gate of the Foundation; and all the people shall be
        in the courtyards of the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let no one enter the house (temple) of the Lord except the priests
        and the Levites who minister; they may enter, for they are holy. And let
        all the people carefully observe the law of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Levites shall surround the [young] king, every man with his weapons
        in his hand; and whoever comes into the temple [breaking through the ranks
        of the guard to get near Joash] is to be killed. You are to be with the king
        when he comes in [from the temple chamber where he is hiding] and when he
        goes out.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Levites and all Judah acted in accordance with everything
        that Jehoiada the priest had commanded; and every man took his men who were
        to resume duty on the Sabbath, with those who were to go off duty on the
        Sabbath, for Jehoiada the priest did not dismiss [any of] the divisions [from
        their duties]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jehoiada the priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears
        and the large and small shields which had been King David\u2019s, which were
        in the house of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He stationed all the people around the king [as guards for him],
        every man with his weapon in his hand, from the right side to the left side
        of the house (temple), by the altar and by the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Athaliah Killed'
      title: Athaliah Killed
      number: 11
      content: "Then they brought out the king\u2019s son and put the crown on him,
        and gave him the testimony [a copy of the Mosaic Law] and made him king.
        And Jehoiada and his sons anointed him and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Athaliah heard the sound of the people running and praising
        the king, she went into the house of the Lord to [see what] the people [were
        doing]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "She looked, and there was the [young] king, standing by his pillar
        at the entrance, and the captains and the trumpeters were beside him. And
        all the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets, and the singers
        with their musical instruments were directing the [singing of] praise. Then
        Athaliah tore her clothes and cried, \u201CTreason! Treason!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds who were
        appointed over the army and said to them, \u201CBring her out between the
        ranks [of soldiers]; and whoever follows her shall be put to death with the
        sword.\u201D For the priest had said, \u201CDo not let her be put to death
        in the temple of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Reforms Carried Out'
      title: Reforms Carried Out
      number: 15
      content: "So they seized Athaliah, and when she arrived at the entrance of
        the Horse Gate of the king\u2019s house (palace), they put her to death there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jehoiada made a covenant between himself, all the people, and
        the king, that they would be the Lord\u2019s people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then all the people went to the house of Baal and tore it down, and
        they smashed its altars and its images to pieces, and killed Mattan, the
        priest of Baal, in front of the altars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also Jehoiada placed the offices and officers of the house of the
        Lord under the authority of the Levitical priests, whom David had [previously]
        assigned over the house of the Lord, to offer the burnt offerings of the
        Lord, as it is written in the Law of Moses, with rejoicing and singing in
        accordance with the order of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jehoiada stationed the gatekeepers [at the gates] of the house of
        the Lord, so that no one would enter who was in any way unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He took the captains of hundreds, the nobles, the rulers of the people,
        and all the people of the land, and brought the king down from the house
        of the Lord; and they came through the upper gate to the king\u2019s house
        (palace) and set the king on the throne of the kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So all the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was quiet after
        Athaliah had been put to death with the sword.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Young Joash Influenced by Jehoiada'
      title: Young Joash Influenced by Jehoiada
      number: 1
      content: "  Joash was seven years old when he became king, and he reigned for
        forty years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zibiah from Beersheba. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Joash did what was right in the sight of the Lord all the days of
        Jehoiada the priest [his uncle]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Faithless Priests'
      title: Faithless Priests
      number: 3
      content: 'Jehoiada took two wives for him, and he fathered sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it came about after this that Joash decided to restore the house
        (temple) of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He gathered the priests and the Levites and said to them, \u201CGo
        out to the cities of Judah and collect money from all Israel to repair the
        house of your God from year to year; and see that you do it quickly.\u201D
        But the Levites did not act quickly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the king called for Jehoiada the high priest and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have you not required the Levites to bring in from Judah and Jerusalem
        the tax for the tent of the testimony which was authorized by Moses, the
        servant of the Lord and the servant of the assembly of Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Temple Repaired'
      title: Temple Repaired
      number: 7
      content: 'For the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken into the
        house of God and also had used all the holy and dedicated things of the house
        of the Lord for the Baals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So at the king\u2019s command they made a chest and set it outside
        by the gate of the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then they made a proclamation in Judah and Jerusalem to bring in
        for the Lord the tax that Moses the servant of God imposed on Israel in the
        wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the officers and all the people rejoiced and brought their tax
        and dropped it into the chest until they had finished [and the chest was
        full]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "It came about that whenever the Levites brought the chest to the
        king\u2019s official, and whenever they saw that there was a large amount
        of money, the king\u2019s secretary and the chief priest\u2019s representative
        would come and empty the chest, and take it, and return it to its place.
        They did this day after day and collected a large amount of money. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who did the work of the service
        of the house of the Lord; and they would hire masons and carpenters (craftsmen)
        and also those who worked in iron and bronze to repair and restore the house
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the workmen labored, and the repair work progressed in their hands;
        and they restored and organized the house of God in accordance with its specifications
        and strengthened it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before
        the king and Jehoiada; and it was [melted down and] made into utensils for
        the house of the Lord, utensils for ministering and for burnt offerings,
        and bowls and utensils of gold and silver. And they offered burnt offerings
        in the house of the Lord continually all the days of Jehoiada.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now when Jehoiada grew old and was full of days, he died. He was
        a hundred and thirty years old at his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They buried him in the City of David among the kings, because he
        had done good [things] in Israel and toward God and His house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now after the death of Jehoiada [the priest, who had hidden Joash],
        the officials of Judah came and bowed down to King Joash; then the king listened
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They abandoned the house of the Lord, the God of their fathers, and
        served the Asherim and the idols; so [God\u2019s] wrath came on Judah and
        Jerusalem for their sin and guilt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Joash Murders Son of Jehoiada'
      title: Joash Murders Son of Jehoiada
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet God sent prophets among them to bring them back to the Lord;
        these prophets testified against them, but they would not listen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the Spirit of God came over Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the
        priest, and he stood above the people and said to them, \u201CThis is what
        God has said: \u2018Why do you transgress the commandments of the Lord so
        that you cannot prosper? Because you have abandoned (turned away from) the
        Lord, He has also abandoned (turned away from) you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So they conspired against Zechariah and stoned him [to death] at
        the command of the king, in the courtyard of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Aram Invades and Defeats Judah'
      title: Aram Invades and Defeats Judah
      number: 22
      content: "Thus Joash the king did not remember the kindness which Jehoiada,
        Zechariah\u2019s father, had shown him, but he murdered his son. And when
        Zechariah was dying, he said, \u201CMay the Lord see this and require an
        accounting!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now it happened at the end of the year, that the army of Aram (Syria)
        went up against Joash. They came to Judah and Jerusalem and killed all the
        leaders among the people and sent all their spoil to the king of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Though the army of the Arameans came with a small company of men,
        the Lord handed over a very large army into their hands, because Joash and
        Judah had abandoned (turned away from) the Lord, the God of their fathers.
        So the Arameans executed judgment against Joash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When they left Joash (for they left him very ill), his own servants
        conspired against him because of the blood of the son of Jehoiada the priest,
        and they murdered him on his bed. So he died, and they buried him in the
        City of David, but they did not bury him in the tombs of the kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The conspirators against Joash were Zabad the son of Shimeath the
        Ammonitess, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the Moabitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Now as to his sons and the many prophecies uttered against him and
        the rebuilding of the house of God, they are written in the commentary on
        the Book of Kings. Then his son Amaziah became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Succeeds Joash in Judah'
      title: Amaziah Succeeds Joash in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jehoaddan
        of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, yet not wholeheartedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When his kingdom was firmly established, he killed his servants who
        had struck down his father the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Amaziah Defeats Edomites'
      title: Amaziah Defeats Edomites
      number: 4
      content: "But he did not kill their children; for he did as it is written in
        the Law, in the Book of Moses, where the Lord commanded, \u201CThe fathers
        shall not die for the children, nor the children die for the fathers, but
        each shall be put to death for his own sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Amaziah assembled [the men of] Judah and appointed them in accordance
        with their fathers\u2019 (ancestors\u2019) households under commanders of
        thousands and of hundreds throughout Judah and Benjamin. He numbered them
        from twenty years old and above and found there to be 300,000 choice men
        fit for war and able to handle spear and shield. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also hired 100,000 brave warriors from Israel for a hundred talents
        of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But a man of God came to him, saying, \u201CO king, do not let this
        army of Israel go with you, for the Lord is not with Israel nor with any
        of the sons of Ephraim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But if you do go [in spite of this warning], be strong and courageous
        for battle; yet God will cause you to stumble and fall before the enemy,
        for God has power to help and to cause people to stumble.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Amaziah said to the man of God, \u201CBut what shall we do about
        the hundred talents which I gave to the troops of Israel?\u201D The man of
        God answered, \u201CThe Lord is able to give you much more than this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Amaziah dismissed the troops that came to him from Ephraim, to
        go home. So their anger was kindled and burned greatly against Judah, and
        they returned home in the heat of anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Amaziah took courage and led his people out to the Valley of
        Salt, and he struck down 10,000 of the men of Seir (Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Judah also captured 10,000 alive and brought them to
        the top of the cliff. They threw them down from the top of the cliff and
        they were all crushed to pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Amaziah Rebuked for Idolatry'
      title: Amaziah Rebuked for Idolatry
      number: 13
      content: 'But the troops whom Amaziah sent back, those not allowed to go with
        him to battle, attacked and raided the cities of Judah, from Samaria to Beth-horon,
        and struck down 3,000 men and took a large amount of spoil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After Amaziah came back from the slaughter of the Edomites, he brought
        the gods of the sons of Seir, and set them up to be his gods, bowed before
        them, and burned incense to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the anger of the Lord burned against Amaziah, and He sent him
        a prophet who said to him, \u201CWhy have you desired the gods of the people
        who did not save their own people from your hand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Amaziah Defeated by Joash of Israel'
      title: Amaziah Defeated by Joash of Israel
      number: 16
      content: "As he was talking, the king said to him, \u201CHave we made you the
        king\u2019s counselor? Stop! Why should you be put to death?\u201D Then the
        prophet stopped and said, \u201CI know that God has decided to destroy you
        because you have done this and have ignored my advice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Amaziah king of Judah took counsel and sent word to Joash the
        son of Jehoahaz the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome [to battle],
        let us face each other.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Joash king of Israel sent word to Amaziah king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CThe [little] thorn bush in Lebanon sent word to the [great] cedar in
        Lebanon, saying, \u2018Give your daughter to my son in marriage.\u2019 But
        a wild beast in Lebanon passed by and trampled down the thorn bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You say, \u2018See, I have struck down and defeated Edom.\u2019 Your
        heart lifts you up to boast [about your victory]. Now stay at home; why should
        you meddle and court disaster so that you, even you, will fall and Judah
        with you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Amaziah would not listen, for it was from God, so that He might
        hand Judah over to Joash because they had desired the gods of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joash king of Israel went up; and he and Amaziah king of Judah
        faced one another at Beth-shemesh, which belonged to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and they fled, every man to his
        tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Joash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son
        of Joash the son of Jehoahaz (Ahaziah), at Beth-shemesh, and brought him
        to Jerusalem and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Ephraim Gate to
        the Corner Gate, 400 cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He took all the gold and silver and all the utensils which were found
        in the house of God with [the doorkeeper] Obed-edom, and the treasures of
        the king\u2019s house (palace), and the hostages, and returned to Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived fifteen years after
        the death of Joash the son of Jehoahaz king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, from the first to the last,
        are they not written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now from the time that Amaziah turned away from following the Lord,
        they conspired against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish; but they
        sent men after him to Lachish and killed him there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Then they brought him on horses and buried him with his fathers in
        the City of [David in] Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Uzziah Succeeds Amaziah in Judah'
      title: Uzziah Succeeds Amaziah in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the people of Judah took Uzziah, who was sixteen years
        old, and made him king in place of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He built Eloth and restored it to Judah after the king [Amaziah]
        slept with his fathers [in death]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Uzziah was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned
        fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jechiliah of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that his father Amaziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Uzziah Succeeds in War'
      title: Uzziah Succeeds in War
      number: 5
      content: 'He continued to seek God in the days of Zechariah, who had understanding
        through the vision of God; and as long as he sought (inquired of, longing
        for) the Lord, God caused him to prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He went out and made war against the Philistines, and broke through
        the wall of Gath, the wall of Jabneh, and the wall of Ashdod; and he built
        cities near Ashdod and [elsewhere] among the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'God helped him against the Philistines, and against the Arabs who
        lived in Gur-baal, and the Meunites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Ammonites paid tribute (money) to Uzziah, and his fame spread
        abroad, even as far as the border of Egypt, for he became very strong. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Uzziah also built towers in Jerusalem at the Corner Gate, the Valley
        Gate, and at the corner buttress [of the wall], and fortified them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He also built towers in the wilderness and dug many cisterns, for
        he had a great deal of livestock, both in the lowlands and in the plain.
        He also had farmers and vinedressers in the hill country and in the fertile
        fields, for he loved the soil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Moreover, Uzziah had an army ready for battle, which went into combat
        by divisions according to the number of their muster as recorded by Jeiel
        the scribe and Maaseiah the official, under the direction of Hananiah, one
        of the king\u2019s commanders. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The total number of the heads of the fathers\u2019 households, of
        valiant men, was 2,600. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Under their command was an army of 307,500, who could wage war with
        great power, to help the king against the enemy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover, Uzziah prepared shields, spears, helmets, body armor, bows,
        and sling stones for the entire army. '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Pride Is Uzziah\u2019s Undoing"
      title: "Pride Is Uzziah\u2019s Undoing"
      number: 15
      content: 'In Jerusalem he made machines of war invented by skillful men to
        be put on the towers and on the [corner] battlements for the purpose of shooting
        arrows and large stones. And his fame spread far, for he was marvelously
        helped until he was strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But when Uzziah became strong, he became so proud [of himself and
        his accomplishments] that he acted corruptly, and he was unfaithful and sinned
        against the Lord his God, for he went into the temple of the Lord to burn
        incense on the altar of incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him eighty priests
        of the Lord, men of courage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They opposed King Uzziah and said to him, \u201CIt is not for you,
        Uzziah, to burn incense to the Lord, but for the priests, the sons of Aaron
        who have been consecrated to burn incense. Get out of the sanctuary, for
        you have been unfaithful and will have no honor from the Lord God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Uzziah, with a censer in his hand to burn incense, was enraged;
        and while he was enraged with the priests, leprosy broke out on his forehead
        before the priests in the house of the Lord, beside the incense altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As Azariah the chief priest and all the priests looked toward him,
        behold, he was leprous on his forehead; and they hurried him out of there,
        and he also hurried to get out because the Lord had stricken him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "King Uzziah was a leper to the day of his death; and, being a leper,
        he lived in a separate house, for he was excluded from the house of the Lord.
        And his son Jotham took charge of the king\u2019s household, judging and
        governing the people of the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, from the first to the last, Isaiah
        the prophet, the son of Amoz, has written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Uzziah slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him
        with his fathers in the burial field of the kings [outside the royal tombs],
        for they said, \u201CHe is a leper.\u201D And his son Jotham became king
        in his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jotham Succeeds Uzziah in Judah'
      title: Jotham Succeeds Uzziah in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  Jotham was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jerushah the daughter
        of Zadok. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that his father Uzziah had done; however, he did not enter the temple of
        the Lord. But the people continued behaving corruptly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He built the upper gate of the house of the Lord, and did extensive
        building on the wall of Ophel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moreover, he built cities in the hill country of Judah, and in the
        forests he built fortresses and towers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also fought with the king of the Ammonites and prevailed over
        them. As a result the Ammonites gave him during that year a hundred talents
        of silver and ten thousand measures each of wheat and of barley. The Ammonites
        also paid him that much in the second year and third year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jotham grew powerful, because he directed his ways before the
        Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars and his ways,
        behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for sixteen years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And Jotham slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him
        in the City of David. Ahaz his son became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Succeeds Jotham in Judah'
      title: Ahaz Succeeds Jotham in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned for
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. He did not do right in the sight of the Lord,
        as his father (forefather) David had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Instead he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and even made
        cast images for the Baals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he burned incense in the Valley of Ben-hinnom and burned his
        sons [as an offering], in accordance with the repulsive acts of the [pagan]
        nations whom the Lord had driven out before the sons (descendants) of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Judah Is Invaded'
      title: Judah Is Invaded
      number: 4
      content: 'He also sacrificed and burned incense on the high places [of pagan
        worship], on the hills and under every green tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the Lord his God handed over Ahaz to the king of Aram (Syria),
        who defeated him and led away a great number [of the people] as captives,
        and brought them to Damascus. And he was also handed over to the king of
        Israel, who struck Judah with a great slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For Pekah son of Remaliah killed 120,000 in Judah in one day, all
        courageous men, because they had abandoned (turned away from) the Lord God
        of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Zichri, a warrior of Ephraim, killed Maaseiah the king\u2019s
        son, and Azrikam the governor of the house, and Elkanah, who was second [in
        power] to the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the sons of Israel led away captive 200,000 of their kinsmen
        [of Judah]\u2014women, sons, and daughters\u2014and they also took a great
        quantity of spoil from them and brought it to Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But a prophet of the Lord was there, whose name was Oded; and he
        went out to meet the army that was returning to Samaria and said to them,
        \u201CBehold, because the Lord, the God of your fathers, was angry with Judah,
        He handed them over to you; but you have killed them in a rage that has reached
        as far as heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now you intend to subjugate the people of Judah and Jerusalem
        as male and female slaves for yourselves. But are you yourselves not guilty
        of transgressions against the Lord your God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now therefore, hear me and return the captives whom you have captured
        from your brothers (fellow descendants of Israel, i.e. Jacob), for the burning
        anger of the Lord is against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then some of the heads of the Ephraimites (Israel)\u2014Azariah the
        son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah the son of Shallum,
        and Amasa the son of Hadlai\u2014took a stand against those who were returning
        from the battle, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and said to them, \u201CYou must not bring the captives in here;
        for we are guilty before the Lord  already, and what you intend to do will
        add more to our sins and our guilt. For our guilt is so great that His burning
        anger is against Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the armed men [of Israel] left the captives and the spoil [of
        Judah] before the officers and all the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Compromise with Assyria'
      title: Compromise with Assyria
      number: 15
      content: "Then the men who were designated by name rose up and took the captives,
        and from the spoil they clothed all those who were naked; they clothed them
        and gave them sandals, and fed them and gave them [something to] drink, anointed
        them [with oil, as was a host\u2019s duty], and led all the feeble ones on
        donkeys, and they brought them to Jericho, the City of Palm Trees, to their
        brothers (fellow descendants of Israel, i.e. Jacob). Then they returned to
        Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time King Ahaz sent word to the king of Assyria [to ask him]
        for help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the Edomites had come again and attacked Judah and led away captives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Philistines had also invaded the cities of the low country and
        of the Negev (the South country) of Judah, and had taken Beth-shemesh, Aijalon,
        Gederoth, and Soco with their villages, and also Timnah with its villages,
        and Gimzo with its villages, and they settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the Lord humbled Judah because of Ahaz king of Israel, for Ahaz
        had allowed unrestrained and undisciplined behavior in Judah and had been
        very unfaithful to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria came against him and harassed
        him instead of strengthening and supporting him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Although Ahaz took a portion [of treasure] from the house of the
        Lord and from the house (palace) of the king and from the leaders, and gave
        it [as tribute] to the king of Assyria, it did not help Ahaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In the time of his distress, this same King Ahaz became yet more
        unfaithful to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus, which had defeated him,
        and he said, \u201CSince the gods of the kings of Aram (Syria) helped them,
        I will sacrifice to them so that they may help me.\u201D But they became
        the ruin and downfall of him and all of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Ahaz collected the utensils of the house of God and he cut them
        in pieces; and he shut the doors of the house of the Lord and made altars
        for himself in every corner of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'In every city of Judah he made high places to burn incense to other
        gods, provoking to anger the Lord, the God of his fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of his acts and of all his ways, from the first to the
        last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And Ahaz slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him in
        the city, in Jerusalem, but they did not bring him into the tombs of the
        kings of Israel. And his son Hezekiah reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Succeeds Ahaz in Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Succeeds Ahaz in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  Hezekiah became king when he was twenty-five years old, and he
        reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Abijah
        the daughter of Zechariah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that David his father (forefather) had done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he opened the
        doors of the house of the Lord [which his father had closed] and repaired
        them [and replaced the gold overlay]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Reforms Begun'
      title: Reforms Begun
      number: 4
      content: 'He brought in the priests and Levites and gathered them into the
        square on the east.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CLevites, listen to me! Now consecrate
        (dedicate) yourselves and consecrate the house of the Lord, the God of your
        fathers, and get the filth [of idol worship] out of the Holy Place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For our fathers have been unfaithful and have done evil in the sight
        of the Lord our God, and they have abandoned Him and have turned their faces
        away from the dwelling place of the Lord, and have turned their backs [toward
        Him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have also closed the doors of the [temple] porch and put out
        the lamps, and they have not burned incense nor offered burnt offerings in
        the Holy Place to the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore the wrath of the Lord has been against Judah and Jerusalem,
        and He has made them an object of terror, of horror, and of hissing, just
        as you see with your own eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold, our fathers have fallen by the sword, and our sons and
        our daughters and our wives are in captivity because of this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now it is in my heart to make a covenant (solemn agreement) with
        the Lord God of Israel, so that His burning anger will turn away from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "My sons, do not be negligent and careless now, for the Lord has chosen
        you to stand in His presence, to attend to His service, and to be His ministers
        and burn incense.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the Levites arose: Mahath the son of Amasai and Joel the son
        of Azariah, from the sons of the Kohathites; from the sons of Merari: Kish
        the son of Abdi, Azariah the son of Jehallelel; from the Gershonites: Joah
        the son of Zimmah and Eden the son of Joah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'from the sons of Elizaphan: Shimri and Jeiel; from the sons of Asaph:
        Zechariah, and Mattaniah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'from the sons of Heman: Jehiel and Shimei; and from the sons of Jeduthun:
        Shemaiah and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They gathered their brothers (fellow Levites) together, consecrated
        themselves, and went in to cleanse the house of the Lord, as the king had
        commanded by the words of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The priests went into the inner part of the house of the Lord to
        cleanse it, and every unclean thing they found in the temple of the Lord
        they brought out to the courtyard of the Lord\u2019s house. Then the Levites
        received it to take out to the Kidron Valley [for disposal]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now they began the consecration on the first [day] of the first month,
        and on the eighth day of the month they came to the porch of the Lord. Then
        for eight days they consecrated the house of the Lord, and on the sixteenth
        day of the first month they finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they went inside to King Hezekiah and said, \u201CWe have cleansed
        the entire house (temple) of the Lord, the altar of burnt offering with all
        of its utensils, and the table of showbread with all its utensils. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Hezekiah Restores Temple Worship'
      title: Hezekiah Restores Temple Worship
      number: 19
      content: "Moreover, we have prepared and consecrated all the utensils which
        King Ahaz had discarded during his reign in his unfaithfulness; and behold,
        they are in front of the altar of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then King Hezekiah arose early and assembled the officials of the
        city, and went up to the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs, and seven male
        goats for a sin offering for the kingdom, the sanctuary, and Judah. He commanded
        the priests, the sons of Aaron, to offer them on the altar of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So they slaughtered the bulls, and the priests took the blood and
        sprinkled it on the altar. They also slaughtered the rams and sprinkled the
        blood on the altar; then they slaughtered the lambs and sprinkled the blood
        on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then they brought the male goats for the sin offering before the
        king and the assembly, and they laid their hands on them [to symbolize the
        transference of their sin]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The priests slaughtered them and cleansed the altar from sin with
        their blood to atone for all Israel, because the king commanded that the
        burnt offering and the sin offering be made for all Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Hezekiah stationed the Levites in the house of the Lord with cymbals,
        with harps, and with lyres, in accordance with the command of David [his
        ancestor] and of Gad the king\u2019s seer, and of Nathan the prophet; for
        the command was from the Lord through His prophets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The Levites stood with the musical instruments of David, and the
        priests with the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then Hezekiah gave the order to offer the burnt offering on the altar.
        And when the burnt offering began, the song to the Lord also began with the
        trumpets accompanied by the instruments of David, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The entire congregation worshiped, the singers also sang, and the
        trumpets sounded; all this continued until the burnt offering was finished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When the burnt offerings were completed, the king and all who were
        present with him bowed down and worshiped [God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Also King Hezekiah and the officials ordered the Levites to exclaim
        praises to the Lord with the words of David and of Asaph the seer. And they
        exclaimed praises with joy, and bowed down and worshiped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Hezekiah said, \u201CNow you have consecrated yourselves to
        the Lord; approach and bring sacrifices and thank offerings into the house
        of the Lord.\u201D And the assembly brought in sacrifices and thank offerings,
        and all those who were willing brought burnt offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The number of the burnt offerings which the assembly brought was
        70 bulls, 100 rams, and 200 lambs. All these were for a burnt offering to
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The consecrated things were 600 bulls and 3,000 sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But there were too few priests and they were unable to skin all the
        burnt offerings; so until the other priests had consecrated themselves, their
        brothers, the Levites, helped them until the work was done. For the Levites
        were more upright in heart and more conscientious than the priests in consecrating
        themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'There were also many burnt offerings with the fat of the peace offerings
        and with the drink offerings for the burnt offerings. So the service of the
        house of the Lord was established again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Then Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced because of what God had
        prepared for the people, for the thing came about suddenly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: All Israel Invited to the Passover'
      title: All Israel Invited to the Passover
      number: 1
      content: '  Hezekiah sent word to all Israel and to Judah and also wrote letters
        to Ephraim and Manasseh to come to the house of the Lord at Jerusalem to
        celebrate the Passover Feast to the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the king and his officials and all the assembly in Jerusalem
        had decided to celebrate the Passover in the second month, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'since they could not celebrate it at that time because a sufficient
        number of priests had not consecrated themselves, nor had the people assembled
        at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus the [decision to set a] new time pleased the king and the entire
        assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they decided to circulate a proclamation throughout Israel, from
        Beersheba to Dan, that the people were to come to celebrate the Passover
        to the Lord God of Israel, at Jerusalem. For they had not celebrated it in
        great numbers as it was prescribed [for a long time]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the runners went throughout Israel and Judah with the letters
        from the hand of the king and his officials, in accordance with the command
        of the king, saying, \u201CO sons (descendants) of Israel, return to the
        Lord God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel (Jacob), so that He will return to
        those of you who escaped and are left from the hand (power) of the kings
        of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Do not be like your fathers and your brothers, who were unfaithful
        to the Lord God of their fathers, so that He made them a horror (lifeless,
        desolate), just as you see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now do not stiffen your neck [becoming obstinate] like your fathers,
        but yield to the Lord and come to His sanctuary which He has sanctified and
        set apart forever, and serve the Lord your God, so that His burning anger
        will turn away from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For if you return to the Lord, your brothers (relatives) and your
        children will find compassion in the presence of those who led them away
        captive and will return to this land. For the Lord your God is gracious and
        merciful, and He will not turn His face away from you if you return to Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the runners (couriers) passed from city to city through the country
        of Ephraim and Manasseh, as far as Zebulun; but the people laughed at them
        with scorn and mocked them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yet some of the men of Asher, Manasseh, and Zebulun humbled themselves
        and came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Passover Reinstituted'
      title: Passover Reinstituted
      number: 12
      content: 'Also the hand of God was on Judah to give them one heart to do that
        which the king and the officials had commanded by the word of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now many people were gathered at Jerusalem to celebrate the Feast
        of Unleavened Bread in the second month; it was a very large assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They took action and removed the [pagan] altars which were in Jerusalem;
        they also removed all the incense altars and threw them into the Brook Kidron
        [the dumping place for the ashes of such repulsive things]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they slaughtered the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of
        the second month. And the priests and the Levites were ashamed of themselves,
        and consecrated themselves and brought burnt offerings to the house of the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They stood at their accustomed stations, in accordance with the Law
        of Moses, the man of God. The priests sprinkled the blood [which they received]
        from the hand of the Levites [on the altar]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For there were many in the assembly who had not consecrated themselves
        [that is, become ceremonially clean and free from all sin]; so the Levites
        had to slaughter the Passover lambs for everyone who was not clean, in order
        to make them holy for the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For the majority of the people, many from Ephraim and Manasseh, Issachar
        and Zebulun, had not purified themselves, and yet they ate the Passover contrary
        to what had been prescribed. For Hezekiah had prayed for them, saying, \u201CMay
        the good Lord pardon "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "everyone who sets his heart to seek God\u2014the Lord God of his
        fathers\u2014even though it is not in accordance with the [ceremonial] purification
        [rules] of the sanctuary.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the Lord listened to Hezekiah and healed the people [of their
        uncleanness]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Israelites who were present in Jerusalem celebrated the Feast
        of Unleavened Bread for seven days with great joy. The Levites and priests
        praised the Lord day after day, singing to the Lord with loud instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Hezekiah spoke encouragingly to all the Levites who showed good understanding
        in the things of the Lord. So the people ate for the appointed seven days,
        sacrificing peace offerings and giving thanks to the Lord God of their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the whole assembly decided to celebrate [the feast] for another
        seven days; and they celebrated it another seven days with joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Hezekiah king of Judah gave to the assembly 1,000 bulls and 7,000
        sheep, and the officials gave the assembly 1,000 bulls and 10,000 sheep.
        And a large number of priests consecrated themselves [for service]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All the assembly of Judah rejoiced, with the priests and the Levites
        and all the assembly that came from Israel, both the sojourners (resident
        aliens, foreigners) who came from the land of Israel and those living in
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So there was great joy in Jerusalem, because there had been nothing
        like this in Jerusalem since the time of Solomon the son of David, king of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then the priests and Levites stood and blessed the people; and their
        voice was heard and their prayer came up to His holy dwelling place, to heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idols Are Destroyed'
      title: Idols Are Destroyed
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when all of this was finished, all Israel who were present
        went out to the cities of Judah, and smashed the [pagan] pillars (obelisks,
        memorial stones) in pieces, cut down the Asherim (wooden symbols of a female
        deity), and tore down the high places and the altars [of idolatry] throughout
        all Judah and Benjamin, as well as in Ephraim and Manasseh, until they had
        destroyed them all. Then all the sons (descendants) of Israel returned to
        their own cities, each to his own property.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Reforms Continued'
      title: Reforms Continued
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hezekiah appointed the divisions of the priests, and the Levites
        by their divisions, each in accordance with his service, both the priests
        and Levites, for burnt offerings and for peace offerings, to minister and
        to give thanks and to praise in the gates of the camp of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Hezekiah also appointed the king\u2019s [personal] portion of his
        goods: for the morning and evening burnt offerings, and the burnt offerings
        for the Sabbaths and for the New Moons and for the appointed feasts, as it
        is written in the Law of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He also told (ordered) the people living in Jerusalem to give the
        portion that was due to the priests and Levites, so that they might [be free
        to] devote themselves to the Law of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "As soon as the king\u2019s order spread, the Israelites gave in abundance
        the first fruits of grain, new wine, [olive] oil, honey, and of all the produce
        of the field; and they brought in the tithe of everything abundantly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Israel and Judah who lived in the cities of Judah also
        brought in the tithe of oxen and sheep, and the tithe of sacred gifts which
        were consecrated to the Lord their God, and placed them in heaps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the third month [at the end of wheat harvest] they began to make
        the heaps, and they finished them in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Hezekiah and the rulers came and saw the heaps, they blessed
        the Lord and His people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Hezekiah questioned the priests and Levites about the heaps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Azariah the high priest of the house of Zadok answered him, \u201CSince
        the people began to bring the offerings into the house of the Lord, we have
        had enough to eat with plenty left over, for the Lord has blessed His people,
        and this great quantity is left over.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Hezekiah told them to prepare rooms [for storage] in the house
        of the Lord, and they prepared them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They faithfully brought in the contributions, the tithes, and the
        sacred (dedicated) things. Conaniah the Levite was in charge of them, and
        Shimei his brother was second [in authority]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah,
        Mahath, and Benaiah were overseers directed by Conaniah and Shimei his brother
        by the appointment of King Hezekiah, and Azariah was the chief officer of
        the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, keeper of the East Gate, was in
        charge of the voluntary offerings to God, to apportion the contributions
        for the Lord and the most holy things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Under his authority were Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah,
        and Shecaniah in the cities of the priests, to distribute faithfully their
        portions to their brothers (relatives) by divisions, whether great or small, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "without regard to their genealogical registration, to the males from
        thirty years old and upward\u2014everyone who entered the house of the Lord
        for his daily obligations\u2014for their service in accordance with their
        duties by their divisions; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "as well as the priests who were registered genealogically according
        to their fathers\u2019 households, and the Levites from twenty years old
        and upward, by their duties and by their divisions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The genealogical registration included all their little children,
        their wives, and their sons and daughters, for the whole assembly, because
        they consecrated themselves faithfully in holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Also for the sons of Aaron, the priests, who were in the pasture
        lands of their cities or in each and every city, there were men who were
        designated by name to give portions to every male among the priests and to
        everyone genealogically registered among the Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is what Hezekiah did throughout Judah; and he did what was good,
        right, and true before the Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Every work which he began in the service of the house of God in keeping
        with the law and the commandment, seeking and inquiring of his God [and longing
        for Him], he did with all his heart and prospered.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Invades Judah'
      title: Sennacherib Invades Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  After these things and this faithfulness, Sennacherib king of Assyria
        came and invaded Judah and besieged the fortified cities, intending to take
        them for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come and that he intended
        to go to war against Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'he decided, together with his officers and his soldiers, to stop
        up the water [supply] from the springs which were outside the city [by enclosing
        them with masonry and concealing them], and they helped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So many people came together, and they stopped up all the springs
        and the brook which flowed [underground] through the region, saying, \u201CWhy
        should the kings of Assyria come and find an abundance of water?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also Hezekiah resolutely set to work and rebuilt all the wall that
        had been broken down, and erected towers on it, and he built another wall
        outside and strengthened the Millo (fortification) in the City of David,
        and made a great number of weapons and shields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also appointed military officers over the people and gathered
        them to him in the square at the city gate, and spoke encouragingly to them,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBe strong and courageous. Do not fear or be dismayed because
        of the king of Assyria, nor because of all the army that is with him; for
        the One with us is greater than the one with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Sennacherib Undermines Hezekiah'
      title: Sennacherib Undermines Hezekiah
      number: 8
      content: "With him there is only an arm of flesh, but with us is the Lord our
        God to help us and to fight our battles.\u201D And the people relied on the
        words of Hezekiah king of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After this, Sennacherib king of Assyria, while he was at Lachish
        [besieging it] with all his forces, sent his servants to Jerusalem, to Hezekiah
        king of Judah, and to all Judah who were at Jerusalem, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says Sennacherib king of Assyria, \u2018In what do you
        trust that you are remaining in Jerusalem under siege? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Is not Hezekiah misleading you in order to let you die by famine
        and thirst, while saying, \u201CThe Lord our God will rescue us from the
        hand of the king of Assyria?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Has the same Hezekiah not taken away his [Baal\u2019s] high places
        and his altars, and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, \u201CYou shall worship
        before [only] one altar and burn incense on it\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do you not know what I and my fathers (ancestors) have done to all
        the peoples of the [other] lands? Were the gods of the nations of those lands
        able to rescue their lands from my hand at all? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who [was there] among all the gods of those nations that my fathers
        utterly destroyed who was able to rescue his people from my hand, that your
        God should be able to rescue you from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So now, do not let Hezekiah deceive or mislead you like this, and
        do not believe him, for no god of any nation or kingdom has been able to
        rescue his people from my hand or the hand of my fathers. How much less will
        your God rescue you from my hand!\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And his servants said even more against the Lord God and against
        His servant Hezekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Assyrian king also wrote letters insulting and taunting the Lord
        God of Israel, and speaking against Him, saying, \u201CAs the gods of the
        nations of other lands have not rescued their people from my hand, so the
        God of Hezekiah will not rescue His people from my hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They shouted it loudly in the language of Judah to the people of
        Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten and terrify them, so that they
        might take the city [without a long siege]. '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer Is Answered"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer Is Answered"
      number: 19
      content: 'They spoke of the God of Jerusalem as [they spoke of] the gods of
        the peoples of the earth, [which are only] the work of the hands of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Hezekiah the king and the prophet Isaiah the son of Amoz prayed
        about this and cried out to heaven [for help]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the Lord sent an angel who destroyed every brave warrior, commander,
        and officer in the camp of the king of Assyria. So the king returned to his
        own land in shame. And when he entered the house (temple) of his god, some
        of his own children killed him there with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Thus the Lord saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from
        the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria and from the hand of all others,
        and He gave them rest on every side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And many brought gifts to the Lord at Jerusalem and valuable presents
        to Hezekiah king of Judah; so from then on he was exalted in the sight of
        all nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In those days Hezekiah became terminally ill; and he prayed to the
        Lord, and He answered him and gave him a [miraculous] sign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Hezekiah did nothing [for the Lord] in return for the benefit
        bestowed on him, because his heart had become proud; therefore God\u2019s
        wrath came on him and on Judah and Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'However, Hezekiah humbled his proud heart, both he and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the Lord did not come on them during the
        days of Hezekiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now Hezekiah had immense wealth and honor; and he made for himself
        treasuries for silver, gold, precious stones, spices, shields, and all kinds
        of delightful articles, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and storehouses for the produce of grain, new wine, and [olive] oil,
        and stalls for all kinds of cattle, and sheepfolds for the flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moreover, he made cities for himself and acquired an abundance of
        flocks and herds, for God gave him very many possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'This same Hezekiah also stopped up the upper outlet of the waters
        of Gihon and channeled them down to the west side of the City of David. Hezekiah
        succeeded in everything that he did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And so in the matter of the envoys of the rulers of Babylon, who
        were sent to him to inquire about the wonder that had happened in the land,
        God left him alone only to test him, in order to know everything that was
        in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah and his godly achievements,
        behold, they are written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of
        Amoz, in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So Hezekiah slept with his fathers [in death] and they buried him
        in the upper section of the tombs of the descendants of David; and all Judah
        and the inhabitants of Jerusalem honored him at his death. And his son Manasseh
        became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh Succeeds Hezekiah in Judah'
      title: Manasseh Succeeds Hezekiah in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for fifty-five years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, like the repulsive acts
        of the [pagan] nations whom the Lord dispossessed before the sons (descendants)
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he rebuilt the [idolatrous] high places which his father Hezekiah
        had torn down; and he set up altars for the Baals and made the Asherim, and
        worshiped all the host of heaven [the sun, the moon, stars and planets] and
        served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He built [pagan] altars in the house of the Lord, of which the Lord
        had said, \u201CMy Name shall be in Jerusalem forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts of the
        house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He made his sons pass through the fire [as an offering to his gods]
        in the Valley of Ben-hinnom; and he practiced witchcraft, used divination,
        and practiced sorcery, and dealt with mediums and spiritists. He did much
        evil in the sight of the Lord, provoking Him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he set the carved image of the idol which he had made in the
        house of God, of which God had said to David and to Solomon his son, \u201CIn
        this house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen from all the tribes of Israel,
        I will put My Name [and the symbol of my Presence] forever; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I will not again remove Israel from the land which I appointed
        for your fathers, if they will only be careful to do everything that I have
        commanded them in regard to all the law, the statutes, and the ordinances
        given through Moses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Manasseh\u2019s Idolatry Rebuked"
      title: "Manasseh\u2019s Idolatry Rebuked"
      number: 9
      content: 'So Manasseh caused Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to sin,
        by doing more evil than the [pagan] nations whom the Lord had destroyed before
        the sons of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Lord spoke to Manasseh and to his people, but they paid no
        attention. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the Lord brought the commanders of the army of the king of Assyria
        against them, and they captured Manasseh with hooks [through his nose or
        cheeks] and bound him with bronze [chains] and took him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when he was in distress, he sought the Lord his God and humbled
        himself greatly before the God of his fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he prayed to Him, He was moved by his entreaty and heard his
        pleading, and brought him back to Jerusalem to his kingdom. Then Manasseh
        knew that the Lord is God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After this he built an outer wall for the City of David on the west
        side of Gihon, in the river valley, to the entrance of the Fish Gate; and
        he encircled the Ophel with it and made it very high. Then he put military
        commanders in all the fortified cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He also removed the foreign gods and the idol from the house of the
        Lord, as well as all the altars which he had built on the mountain of the
        house of the Lord and in Jerusalem; and he threw them outside the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then he set up the altar of the Lord and sacrificed peace offerings
        and thank offerings on it; and he ordered Judah to serve the Lord God of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yet the people still sacrificed on the high places, but only to the
        Lord their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, and his prayer to his God,
        and the words of the seers who spoke to him in the name of the Lord God of
        Israel, behold, they are among the records of the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'His prayer also and how God heard him, and all his sin, his unfaithfulness,
        and the sites on which he built high places and set up the Asherim and the
        carved images, before he humbled himself, behold, they are written in the
        records of the Hozai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Amon Becomes King in Judah'
      title: Amon Becomes King in Judah
      number: 20
      content: 'So Manasseh slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him
        in [the garden of] his own house. And his son Amon became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for two years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, just as his father Manasseh
        had done. Amon sacrificed to all the carved images which his father Manasseh
        had made, and he served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Further, he did not humble himself before the Lord as his father
        Manasseh [finally] had done, but Amon multiplied his guilt and his sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And his servants conspired against him and killed him in his own
        house (palace). '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But the people of the land struck down all those who had conspired
        against King Amon, and they made his son Josiah king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Succeeds Amon in Judah'
      title: Josiah Succeeds Amon in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for thirty-one years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did what was right in the sight of the Lord, and walked in the
        ways of David his father (forefather) and did not turn aside either to the
        right or to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was still young (sixteen),
        he began to seek after and inquire of the God of his father David; and in
        the twelfth year he began to purge Judah and Jerusalem of the high places,
        the Asherim, and the carved and cast images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They tore down the altars of the Baals in his presence; he cut to
        pieces the incense altars that were high above them; he also smashed the
        Asherim and the carved images and the cast images to pieces, and ground them
        to dust and scattered it on the graves of those who had sacrificed to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Josiah burned the bones of the [pagan] priests on their altars
        and purged and cleansed Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, Simeon, and as far as Naphtali,
        in their surrounding ruins, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Josiah Repairs the Temple'
      title: Josiah Repairs the Temple
      number: 7
      content: 'he tore down the altars and beat and crushed the Asherim and the
        carved images into powder, and cut to pieces all the incense altars throughout
        the land of Israel. Then he returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "In the eighteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign, when he had purged
        the land and the [Lord\u2019s] house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah,
        and Maaseiah the governor of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder
        (secretary), to repair the house of the Lord his God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When they came to Hilkiah the high priest, they delivered the money
        that had been brought into the house of God, which the Levites, who guarded
        the doors, had collected from Manasseh and Ephraim, and from all the remnant
        of Israel, and from all Judah and Benjamin, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then they gave it to the workmen who were appointed over the house
        of the Lord, and the workmen who were working in the house of the Lord gave
        it [to others] to repair and restore the house (temple). '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They in turn gave it to the carpenters and builders to buy quarried
        stone and timber for couplings (trusses, braces) and to make beams for the
        houses which the kings of Judah had let go to ruin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The men did the work faithfully with foremen over them to supervise
        and inspect [their work]: Jahath and Obadiah, the Levites of the sons of
        Merari, and Zechariah and Meshullam of the sons of the Kohathites, and the
        Levites, all who were skillful with musical instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Hilkiah Discovers Lost Book of the Law'
      title: Hilkiah Discovers Lost Book of the Law
      number: 13
      content: 'They were also in charge of the burden bearers [who carried heavy
        loads], and supervised all the workmen in any kind of service; and some of
        the Levites were scribes and officials and gatekeepers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When they were bringing out the money which had been brought into
        the house of the Lord, Hilkiah the priest found the Book of the Law of the
        Lord  given by Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Hilkiah told Shaphan the scribe, \u201CI have found the Book of the
        Law in the house of the Lord.\u201D And he gave the book to Shaphan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Shaphan brought the book to the king, but [first] reported further
        to him, \u201CYour servants are doing everything that was entrusted to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They have emptied out the money that was found in the house of the
        Lord, and have delivered it into the hands of the overseers and the workmen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Shaphan the scribe told the king, \u201CHilkiah the priest has
        given me a book.\u201D And Shaphan read from it in the presence of the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When the king heard the words of the Law, he tore his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon
        the son of Micah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the king, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Huldah, the Prophetess, Speaks'
      title: Huldah, the Prophetess, Speaks
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of the Lord for me and for those who are left in
        Israel and in Judah in regard to the words of the book which has been found;
        for great is the wrath of the Lord which has been poured out on us because
        our fathers have not kept and obeyed the word of the Lord, to act in accordance
        with everything that is written in this book.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Hilkiah and those whom the king had told went to Huldah the prophetess,
        the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath, the son of Hasrah, keeper of the
        wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem, in the Second Quarter); and they spoke
        to her about this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And she answered them, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel:
        \u2018Tell the man who sent you to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, I am bringing evil on this place
        and on its inhabitants, all the curses that are written in the book which
        they have read in the presence of the king of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Because they have abandoned (rejected) Me and have burned incense
        to other gods, in order to provoke Me to anger with all the works of their
        hands, My wrath will be poured out on this place and it will not be extinguished.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But you shall say the following to King Josiah of Judah, who sent
        you to inquire of the Lord: \u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel, concerning
        the words which you have heard, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBecause your heart was gentle and penitent and you humbled
        yourself before God when you heard His words against this place and its inhabitants,
        and humbled yourself before Me, and tore your clothes and wept before Me,
        I also have heard you,\u201D declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will gather you to your fathers [in death], and you
        shall be gathered to your grave in peace, and your eyes shall not see all
        the evil which I am going to bring on this place and on its inhabitants.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So they brought back word to the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the king sent word and gathered all the elders of Judah and
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Josiah\u2019s Good Reign"
      title: "Josiah\u2019s Good Reign"
      number: 30
      content: 'And the king went up to the house of the Lord with all the men of
        Judah, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests, the Levites, and all the
        people, from the greatest to the least; and he read aloud so they could hear
        all the words of the Book of the Covenant which was found in the house of
        the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then the king stood in his place and made a covenant before the Lord\u2014to
        walk after (obey) the Lord, and to keep His commandments, His testimonies,
        and His statutes with all his heart and with all his soul, to perform the
        words of the covenant written in this book. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Further, he made all who were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin stand
        [with him, in confirmation of it]. So the inhabitants of Jerusalem acted
        in accordance with the covenant of God, the God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Josiah removed all the [pagan] repulsive things from all the lands
        belonging to the sons (descendants) of Israel, and made all who were present
        in Israel serve the Lord their God. Throughout his lifetime they did not
        turn from following the Lord God of their fathers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Passover Observed Again'
      title: The Passover Observed Again
      number: 1
      content: '  Josiah celebrated the Passover to the Lord in Jerusalem; they slaughtered
        the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He appointed the priests to their positions and encouraged them in
        the service of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "To the Levites who taught all Israel and were holy to the Lord he
        said, \u201CPut the holy ark in the house (temple) which Solomon the son
        of David king of Israel built; it shall not be a burden [carried] on your
        shoulders any longer. Now serve the Lord your God and His people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Prepare yourselves according to your fathers\u2019 (ancestors\u2019)
        households by your divisions, in accordance with the instructions of David
        king of Israel, and the instructions of his son Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And stand in the holy place [of the priests] according to the sections
        of the fathers\u2019 households of your fellow kinsmen the lay people, and
        according to the Levites, by division of [the families of] a father\u2019s
        household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Slaughter the Passover lambs and consecrate yourselves, and prepare
        for your fellow countrymen to carry out (obey) the word of the Lord  given
        by Moses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Josiah contributed to the lay people, to all who were present,
        flocks of lambs and young goats numbering 30,000, all as Passover offerings,
        and 3,000 bulls\u2014these were from the king\u2019s property. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'His officers also contributed a voluntary offering to the people,
        the priests and the Levites. Hilkiah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, the officials
        of the house of God, gave to the priests for the Passover offerings 2,600
        from the flocks [of lambs and young goats], and 300 bulls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethanel, his brothers, and Hashabiah
        and Jeiel and Jozabad, officers of the Levites, contributed to the Levites
        for the Passover offerings 5,000 from the flocks [of lambs and young goats],
        and 500 bulls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the service was ready, the priests stood in their [assigned]
        places and the Levites by their divisions, in accordance with the king\u2019s
        command. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They slaughtered the Passover lambs, and while the priests sprinkled
        the blood received from their hand, the Levites skinned the animals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they removed the burnt offerings, to distribute them to the
        sections of the fathers\u2019 households of the lay people to offer to the
        Lord, as it is written in the Book of Moses. They did the same with the bulls. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they roasted the Passover lambs on the fire according to the ordinance;
        and they cooked the holy offerings in pots, in kettles, and in pans, and
        quickly brought them to all the lay people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Afterward the Levites prepared for themselves and for the priests,
        because the priests, the sons of Aaron, were busy offering the burnt offerings
        and the fat until night; so the Levites prepared for themselves and for the
        priests, the sons of Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The singers, the sons of Asaph, were also in their places in accordance
        with the command of David, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun the king\u2019s seer;
        and the gatekeepers at each gate did not need to leave their service, because
        their kinsmen the Levites prepared for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So all the service of the Lord was prepared on that day to celebrate
        the Passover, and to offer burnt offerings on the altar of the Lord, in accordance
        with the command of King Josiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Thus the sons of Israel who were present celebrated the Passover
        at that time, and the Feast of Unleavened Bread for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'No Passover like it had been celebrated in Israel since the days
        of Samuel the prophet; nor had any of the kings of Israel celebrated such
        a Passover as Josiah did with the priests, the Levites, all Judah and Israel
        who were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Josiah Dies in Battle'
      title: Josiah Dies in Battle
      number: 19
      content: "In the eighteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign this Passover was celebrated.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Neco king of
        Egypt came up to make war at Carchemish on the Euphrates, and Josiah went
        out to meet him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Neco sent messengers to Josiah, saying, \u201CWhat business do
        we have with each other, O King of Judah? I am not coming against you today,
        but against the house with which I am at war, and God has ordered me to hurry.
        Stop for your own sake from interfering with God who is with me, so that
        He will not destroy you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet Josiah would not turn away from him, but disguised himself in
        order to fight against him. He did not listen to the words of Neco from the
        mouth of God, but came to fight against him on the plain of Megiddo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The archers shot King Josiah, and the king said to his servants,
        \u201CTake me away, for I am badly wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So his servants took him out of the chariot and carried him in the
        second chariot which he had, and brought him to Jerusalem where he died and
        was buried in the tombs of his fathers. All Judah and Jerusalem mourned for
        Josiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Jeremiah sung a lament (funeral song) for Josiah, and all the
        male and female singers have spoken about Josiah in their laments to this
        day. They made the songs an ordinance in Israel; behold, they are written
        in the Lamentations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and his deeds of devotion and
        godly achievements as written in the Law of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: and his acts, from the first to the last, behold, they are written
        in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoahaz, Jehoiakim, then Jehoiachin Rule'
      title: Jehoahaz, Jehoiakim, then Jehoiachin Rule
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the people of the land took Joahaz the son of Josiah, and
        made him king in Jerusalem in place of his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Joahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned
        [only] three months in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king of Egypt deposed him at Jerusalem, and imposed a fine
        on the land of a hundred talents of silver and one talent of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The king of Egypt made Eliakim, the brother of Joahaz, king over
        Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. But Neco took Joahaz
        his brother, and brought him to Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for eleven years in Jerusalem; and he did evil in the sight of the Lord his
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against him and bound him
        with bronze [chains] to take him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar also brought some of the articles of the house (temple)
        of the Lord to Babylon and put them in his temple there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim and the repulsive acts which
        he committed, and what was found against him, behold, they are written in
        the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah. And his son Jehoiachin became
        king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Captivity in Babylon Begun'
      title: Captivity in Babylon Begun
      number: 9
      content: 'Jehoiachin was eight[teen] years old when he became king, and he
        reigned for three months and ten days in Jerusalem, and he did evil in the
        sight of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Zedekiah Rules in Judah'
      title: Zedekiah Rules in Judah
      number: 10
      content: 'Now at the turn of the year [in the spring], King Nebuchadnezzar
        sent word and had him brought to Babylon with the valuable articles of the
        house of the Lord, and made his brother Zedekiah king over Judah and Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for eleven years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord his God; he did not humble himself
        before Jeremiah the prophet, who spoke for the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar who had made him swear
        allegiance by God. He stiffened his neck and hardened his heart against turning
        to the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Also, all the officials of the priests and the people were very unfaithful,
        following all the repulsive acts of the [pagan] nations; and they defiled
        the house of the Lord which He had sanctified in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord, the God of their fathers, sent word to them again and again
        by His messengers, because He had compassion on His people and on His dwelling
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But they kept mocking the messengers of God and despising His words
        and scoffing at His prophets until the wrath of the Lord arose against His
        people, until there was no remedy or healing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore He brought the king of the Chaldeans against them, who
        killed their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary, and
        had no compassion on young man or virgin, old man or infirm; He gave them
        all into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And as for all the articles of the house of God, great and small,
        and the treasures of the house of the Lord, and the treasures of the king
        and of his officials, he brought them all to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they burned the house of God and tore down the wall of Jerusalem,
        and burned all its fortified buildings with fire, and destroyed all its valuable
        articles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He deported to Babylon those who had escaped from the sword; and
        they were servants to him and to his sons until the kingdom of Persia was
        established there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Cyrus Permits Return'
      title: Cyrus Permits Return
      number: 21
      content: 'to fulfill the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah, until the
        land had restored its Sabbaths; for as long as the land lay desolate it kept
        Sabbath until seventy years were complete.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia\u2014in order to fulfill
        the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah\u2014the Lord stirred up the
        spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he sent a proclamation throughout
        his kingdom, and also put it in writing, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThus says Cyrus king of Persia: \u2018The Lord, the God of
        heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth, and He has appointed
        me to build Him a house in Jerusalem, which is in Judah. Whoever there is
        among you of all His people, may the Lord his God be with him, and let him
        go up [to Jerusalem]!\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
